ong> Frame-by-Frame Animation</h2>\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Toon Boom Animate, Photoshop, After Effects, Wacom Tablet\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a hand-drawn, frame-by-frame animation. The story all starts with our character finding an innocent umbrella. But when a gust of wind comes up, he gets blown into the sky and floats all day. He eventually falls asleep and drifts back to the ground. Upon waking up, he wonders what the whole thing was about – and shrugs it off as a dream, walking away. Feel free to come up with your own interpretation!\r\n\r\n<img style=\"display:none;visibility:hidden;\" alt=\"frame-by-frame animation\" />','Flyaway Dreams','What happens if you get whisked away by an umbrella?','publish','closed','closed','','flyaway-dreams','','','2014-07-06 14:24:03','2014-07-06 20:24:03','',0,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=166',0,'project','',0),(167,1,'2014-07-06 13:25:28','2014-07-06 19:25:28','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/29126262?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/29126262\" target=\"_blank\">Logo Build</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n<h2 class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Category:</strong> Motion Design</h2>\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> After Effects, Illustrator\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\n\nThis is a logo build I animated for one of my university After Effects classes. I didn\'t design the logo, but recreated it in Illustrator and later animated it in After Effects. In the animation, I wanted to convey the natural quality of the product, both in the animation itself (clean, smooth, growing, light) and the sound design (birds).\n\n*This piece has no tie to the company Clean Conscience LTD and is not approved or supported by them.','Logo Build','Six-second animated logo.','inherit','open','open','','125-autosave-v1','','','2014-07-06 13:25:28','2014-07-06 19:25:28','',125,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/13/125-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(169,1,'2013-07-13 08:53:13','2013-07-13 14:53:13','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/30769977?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0&amp;color=c9ff23\" height=\"675\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\n\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/30769977\" target=\"_blank\">Flyaway Dreams</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.\n\n<b>Category:</b> Animation\n<b>Created Using:</b> Toon Boom Animate, Photoshop, After Effects, Wacom Tablet\n<b>Date:</b> 2011\n\nThis is a hand-drawn, frame-by-frame animation. In this story, the character finds an umbrella, gets blown into the sky, floats all day, falls asleep, drifts back to the ground, wakes up, and wonders what the whole thing was about – he shrugs it off as a dream and walks away. Feel free to come up with your own interpretation!','Flyaway Dreams','','inherit','open','open','','166-revision-v1','','','2013-07-13 08:53:13','2013-07-13 14:53:13','',166,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/13/166-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(171,1,'2013-07-12 06:30:46','2013-07-12 12:30:46','<h2 class=\"firstH1\">Rusalka: The Little Mermaid Story – Set Backdrop Motion Design Videos</h2>\r\nThis is one of 16 videos I made for the University of British Columbia\'s production of Antonín Dvorák\'s opera Rusalka: The Little Mermaid Story, February 9-12, 2012. The videos were projected onto the back of the set behind the stage. I made them in After Effects, using various effects and particles.\r\n\r\nHere\'s one of the videos, shortened a bit:\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/38334568?color=c9ff23\" height=\"675\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/38334568\">Rusalka O