\n<iframe src=\"http://dl.dropbox.com/u/44105561/basic_interactivity2/applet/index.html\" height=\"664\" width=\"660\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Processing / Interactive / Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Processing\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nI made this interactive piece using <a href=\"http://processing.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Processing</a>, an open-source programming language and environment for people who want to create images, animations and interactions.\r\n\r\nHere are some examples of screenshots I took after playing with my Processing applet:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-143\" alt=\"Processing 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing1.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-148\" alt=\"Processing 6\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing6.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-147\" alt=\"Processing 5\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing5.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-144\" alt=\"Processing 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing2.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-146\" alt=\"Processing 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing4.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-145\" alt=\"Processing 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing3.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />','Build it Up','','inherit','open','open','','142-revision-v1','','','2013-07-13 08:05:36','2013-07-13 14:05:36','',142,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/13/142-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(312,1,'2013-07-13 11:28:09','2013-07-13 17:28:09','This was a digital art installation presented for the First Friday Art Walk in downtown Missoula, Montana. It was a collaboration between my fellow University of Montana Media Arts students Lindy Jones, Sari Jones, Preston Schulz, Chelsey Von Ehrenkrook, and myself (aka \"The Dream Team\").\r\n<h2>Vertical Projection, Large Stacked Boxes, Lantern with Spotlight</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-130\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption1.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Stacked Boxes with Spotlight and LED Lightstrip</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-131\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption2.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Main Projection Animation</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-132\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption3.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" />\r\n<h2>Stacked Boxes with LED Lightstrip, Lantern with Spotlight, Bar</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-133\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption4.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Televisions with Animations, Lantern with Spotlight</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-134\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 5\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption5.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Televisions, Lantern with Spotlight, Vertical Projection, Stacked Boxes</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-135\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 6\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption6.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Small Stacked Boxes</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-138\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 9\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption9.jpg\" width=\"464\" height=\"696\" />\r\n<h2>\"The Dream Team\"</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-136\" alt=\"The Dream Team\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption7.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" />\r\n<h2>Advertising Poster</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-137\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption Poster\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption8.jpg\" width=\"464\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2>Main Animation Projection</h2>\r\nThe animation is 10 1/2 minutes long, but feel free to scrub through it! Some of the pizzaz of the original color was lost in the compression. :(\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/24902526?color=cdda57\" height=\"531\" width=\"720\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/24902526\" target=\"_blank\">The Bad Contraption: Main Video</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vertical Animation Projection</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/24901626?color=cdda57\" height=\"400\" width=\"226\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/24901626\" target=\"_blank\">The Bad Contraption: Particles</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Installation Video</h2>\r\nThe spotlights on the wall behind the boxes and on the giant paper lanterns weren\'t up yet, so the video is dark, less colorful and doesn\'t look like the finished product. :(\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/18094025?color=cdda57\" height=\"366\" width=\"650\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/18094025\" target=\"_blank\">The Bad Contraption</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Digital Art Installation / Motion Design / Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, After Effects, LED spotlights &amp; lightstrips, paper lanterns, boxes, duct tape, paper, TVs, projectors\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nOur goal for The Bad Contraption was to create a space in which people could get lost; a surreal, topsy-turvy world.\r\n\r\nIt consisted of two animations projected onto the walls, large stacks of boxes with patterns taped onto them stacked around the room, colored LED lightstrips and spotlights, huge hanging paper lanterns, five televisions which also showed the animations, and piles upon piles of small pink and white boxes viewers could interact and play with. It was held at the Badlander Bar.\r\n\r\nPhoto credits: Jesse Spaulding, Sari Jones, and Ali Gray. Animation Video Credits: The Dream Team. Video credit: Jesse Spaulding.','The Bad Contraption','','inherit','open','open','','129-revision-v1','','','2013-07-13 11:28:09','2013-07-13 17:28:09','',129,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/13/129-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(313,1,'2013-07-13 07:37:02','2013-07-13 13:37:02','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/41753612?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/41753612\" target=\"_blank\">Concentric</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Motion Design / 3D\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Cinema 4D, After Effects\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nThis was my last project for UM Media Arts, but done for an after-the-fact special topics 3D Animation class. It\'s based on the awesome video Spherikal (<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/39792837\" target=\"_blank\">vimeo.com/39792837</a>), which I did following GreyScaleGorilla\'s tutorial (<a href=\"http://greyscalegorilla.com/blog/2012/04/clones-step-effector-and-atom-array-tutorial-for-cinema-4d/\" target=\"_blank\">greyscalegorilla.com/blog/2012/04/clones-step-effector-and-atom-array-tutorial-for-cinema-4d/</a>), with a few touches of my own.\r\n\r\nMusic: \"The Sun is Scheduled to Come out Tomorrow\" by Chris Zabriskie (<a href=\"http://chriszabriskie.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chriszabriskie.com</a>).','Concentric','','inherit','open','open','','127-revision-v1','','','2013-07-13 07:37:02','2013-07-13 13:37:02','',127,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/13/127-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(314,1,'2013-07-13 07:32:48','2013-07-13 13:32:48','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/29126262?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/29126262\" target=\"_blank\">Logo Build</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> After Effects, Illustrator\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a logo build I animated for one of my university After Effects classes. I didn\'t design the logo, but recreated it in Illustrator and later animated it in After Effects.\r\n\r\n*This piece has no tie to the company Clean Conscience LTD and is not approved or supported by them.','Logo Build','','inherit','open','open','','125-revision-v1','','','2013-07-13 07:32:48','2013-07-13 13:32:48','',125,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/13/125-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(315,1,'2013-07-13 07:30:24','2013-07-13 13:30:24','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/32268385?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/32268385\" target=\"_blank\">Title Sequence</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation / Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects, Logic\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a fake title sequence I designed and animated for an After Effects class. The only real person credited in the title sequence is me, and I made up the film and film name, as well.\r\n\r\nIn creating this piece, I was going for something fun, colorful, jazzy, and full of animation.\r\n\r\nThe music is \"Rythme Gitan\" by Latché Swing <a href=\"http://www.jamendo.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">(jamendo.com/en/artist/latche_swing_(3))</a>.\r\n<h2>Storyboards</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-123\" alt=\"Title Sequence Storyboards\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/title_sequence_storyboards.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"334\" />','Title Sequence','','inherit','open','open','','122-revision-v1','','','2013-07-13 07:30:24','2013-07-13 13:30:24','',122,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/13/122-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(316,1,'2013-07-13 07:17:07','2013-07-13 13:17:07','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/16623351?color=cdda57\" height=\"491\" width=\"872\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/16623351\" target=\"_blank\">Overgrown</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Paper, Chair, Lamp, Photoshop, Final Cut, Logic\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is an experimental stop motion animation I did for my University of Montana Media Arts animation class.\r\n\r\nIt consists of dozens of little creepy tree paper cutouts that I taped to a chair, lit with a lamp, and then photographed the shadows. I used a replacement animation technique. I made the title by cutting out the words from a piece of paper, holding it up to a light, taking the picture, then inverting the black and white.\r\n\r\nI wanted to experiment with different shadows to create a unique, abstract stop motion animation. The soundtrack is a custom sound design piece I created in Logic.\r\n<h2>Trees</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-119\" alt=\"Overgrown Trees\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/overgrown_trees.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n<h2>Storyboards</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-117\" alt=\"Overgrown Storyboards\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/overgrown_storyboards.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"673\" />\r\n<h2>Tree &amp; Animation Setup Concepts</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-118\" alt=\"Overgrown Tree Concepts\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/overgrown_tree_concepts.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />','Overgrown','','inherit','open','open','','116-revision-v1','','','2013-07-13 07:17:07','2013-07-13 13:17:07','',116,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/13/116-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(317,1,'2013-07-13 07:12:05','2013-07-13 13:12:05','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/15644555?color=cdda57\" height=\"470\" width=\"752\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/15644555\" target=\"_blank\">Bounce</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Index Cards, Pencil &amp; Sharpie, Scanner, Final Cut\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a flip book I made for my University of Montana Media Arts animation class.\r\n\r\nI first drew out 128 pictures on index cards, outlined then in Sharpie, scanned them in one by one (which took a LONG time), and finally edited them together and added audio in Final Cut.\r\n<h2>Card Stack</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-112\" alt=\"Bounce Card Stack\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bounce_card_stack.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />\r\n<h2>Cards Example</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-113\" alt=\"Bounce Cards Example\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bounce_cards.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />','Bounce','','inherit','open','open','','111-revision-v1','','','2013-07-13 07:12:05','2013-07-13 13:12:05','',111,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/13/111-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(318,1,'2013-07-12 17:49:32','2013-07-12 23:49:32','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/15852498?color=cdda57\" height=\"471\" width=\"856\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/15852498\" target=\"_blank\">A Simple Gift</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, Final Cut\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a fun little animation I did for a Media Arts animation class. I made it by saving 227 individual jpegs out of a Photoshop document I created and then editing them together and adding audio in Final Cut. It\'s essentially a digital flipbook.\r\n\r\nThe music is Kate Nash\'s \"Merry Happy.\"\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Frame Sequence Demonstration</h2>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-92\" alt=\"A Simple Gift Frames Demonstration\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/a_simple_gift_frames_demonstration.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"333\" />\r\n\r\nHere is a sample of three frames, each consisting of a separate jpeg, from three different scenes.','A Simple Gift','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-v1','','','2013-07-12 17:49:32','2013-07-12 23:49:32','',86,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/12/86-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(319,1,'2013-07-12 17:16:53','2013-07-12 23:16:53','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-83\" alt=\"Typography Poster\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/typography_poster_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"485\" height=\"749\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nThis is an informational poster I made for a fake event as part of a university typography class.\r\n\r\nWe could only use simple graphical elements: the main concentration was supposed to be on letterform and manipulating the layout of text on the page to create something interesting.\r\n\r\nThis piece are not tied to any of the real organizations portrayed on the posters in any way.','Typography Poster','','inherit','open','open','','82-revision-v1','','','2013-07-12 17:16:53','2013-07-12 23:16:53','',82,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/12/82-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(320,1,'2013-07-12 17:13:09','2013-07-12 23:13:09','<img class=\"size-full wp-image-50 aligncenter\" alt=\"Wine by Moonlight\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/wine_by_moonlight_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"582\" height=\"900\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date: </strong>2011\r\n\r\nDesigned for Sapore Restaurant and Bar in Missoula, Montana for their weekly wine-tasting event.\r\n\r\nThe goal of the poster was to portray the uniqueness of this particular wine-centered event, as the room overlooks the rest of downtown Missoula from up on the 3rd story.\r\n\r\nI designed the concept, layout and graphics for the poster.','Wine by Moonlight','graphic design','inherit','open','open','','19-revision-v1','','','2013-07-12 17:13:09','2013-07-12 23:13:09','',19,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/12/19-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2013-07-14 17:20:19','2013-07-14 23:20:19','<img class=\"size-full wp-image-50 aligncenter\" alt=\"Wine by Moonlight\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/wine_by_moonlight_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"582\" height=\"900\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date: </strong>2011\r\n\r\nDesigned for Sapore Restaurant and Bar in Missoula, Montana for their weekly wine-tasting event.\r\n\r\nThe goal of the poster was to portray the uniqueness of this particular wine-centered event, as the room overlooks the rest of downtown Missoula from up on the 3rd story.\r\n\r\nI designed the concept, layout and graphics for the poster.','Wine by Moonlight','graphic design','inherit','open','open','','19-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:20:19','2013-07-14 23:20:19','',19,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/19-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(322,1,'2013-07-14 17:12:33','2013-07-14 23:12:33','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/34098363?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/34098363\" target=\"_blank\">Lumiere de l\'Amour</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, After Effects, Cinema 4D, Wacom Tablet\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is the story of how streetlights guide two wandering robots toward each other through a surreal, ethereal world. As the main character robot sees glimpses on its screen of the other robot wandering and interacting with its own streetlights, each light compels the two to keep going and to come together.\r\n\r\nThis is my final project as a Media Arts major at the University of Montana. My partner <a href=\"http://www.wesleymeeks.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Wesley Meeks</a> and I worked on this project for about a month, from initial concepting to final render. Crunch time! We love how it turned out, though.\r\n\r\nTo see which roles I played in the project, please view the credits at the end of the animation.\r\n<h2>Initial Stylesheet</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-106\" alt=\"Lumiere Initial Stylesheet\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/lumiere_stylesheet.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"506\" />\r\n<h2>Character Concepts</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-102\" alt=\"Lumiere Character Concepts\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/lumiere_character_concept.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"506\" />\r\n<h2>Finished Digital Sketch &amp; Animation Concepts</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-103\" alt=\"Lumiere Animation Concepts\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/lumiere_scene_example.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"506\" />\r\n<h2>Storyboards</h2>\r\n[one_half]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-104\" alt=\"Lumiere Storyboard 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/lumiere_storyboard1.jpg\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-105\" alt=\"Lumiere Storyboard 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/lumiere_storyboard2.jpg\" width=\"100%\" />\r\n[/one_half_last]','Lumiere de l\'Amour','','inherit','open','open','','90-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:12:33','2013-07-14 23:12:33','',90,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/90-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(323,1,'2013-07-14 17:18:11','2013-07-14 23:18:11','This was a digital art installation presented for the First Friday Art Walk in downtown Missoula, Montana. It was a collaboration between my fellow University of Montana Media Arts students Lindy Jones, Sari Jones, Preston Schulz, Chelsey Von Ehrenkrook, and myself (aka \"The Dream Team\").\r\n<h2>Vertical Projection, Large Stacked Boxes, Lantern with Spotlight</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-130\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption1.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Stacked Boxes with Spotlight and LED Lightstrip</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-131\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption2.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Main Projection Animation</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-132\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption3.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" />\r\n<h2>Stacked Boxes with LED Lightstrip, Lantern with Spotlight, Bar</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-133\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption4.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Televisions with Animations, Lantern with Spotlight</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-134\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 5\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption5.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Televisions, Lantern with Spotlight, Vertical Projection, Stacked Boxes</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-135\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 6\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption6.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Small Stacked Boxes</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-138\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 9\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption9.jpg\" width=\"464\" height=\"696\" />\r\n<h2>\"The Dream Team\"</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-136\" alt=\"The Dream Team\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption7.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" />\r\n<h2>Advertising Poster</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-137\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption Poster\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption8.jpg\" width=\"464\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2>Main Animation Projection</h2>\r\nThe animation is 10 1/2 minutes long, but feel free to scrub through it! Some of the pizzaz of the original color was lost in the compression. :(\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/24902526?color=cdda57\" height=\"531\" width=\"720\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/24902526\" target=\"_blank\">The Bad Contraption: Main Video</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vertical Animation Projection</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/24901626?color=cdda57\" height=\"400\" width=\"226\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/24901626\" target=\"_blank\">The Bad Contraption: Particles</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Installation Video</h2>\r\nThe spotlights on the wall behind the boxes and on the giant paper lanterns weren\'t up yet, so the video is dark, less colorful and doesn\'t look like the finished product. :(\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/18094025?color=cdda57\" height=\"366\" width=\"650\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/18094025\" target=\"_blank\">The Bad Contraption</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Digital Art Installation / Motion Design / Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, After Effects, LED spotlights &amp; lightstrips, paper lanterns, boxes, duct tape, paper, TVs, projectors\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nOur goal for The Bad Contraption was to create a space in which people could get lost; a surreal, topsy-turvy world.\r\n\r\nIt consisted of two animations projected onto the walls, large stacks of boxes with patterns taped onto them stacked around the room, colored LED lightstrips and spotlights, huge hanging paper lanterns, five televisions which also showed the animations, and piles upon piles of small pink and white boxes viewers could interact and play with. It was held at the Badlander Bar.\r\n\r\nPhoto credits: Jesse Spaulding, Sari Jones, and Ali Gray. Animation Video Credits: The Dream Team. Video credit: Jesse Spaulding.','The Bad Contraption','','inherit','open','open','','129-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:18:11','2013-07-14 23:18:11','',129,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/129-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(324,1,'2013-07-14 17:17:34','2013-07-14 23:17:34','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-159\" alt=\"Photographer Website\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photographer_website_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Web Design / Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nThis is a website I designed for a talented photographer in the Missoula area. She has asked to remain anonymous until the site goes live, so that is the reason for the large white circle in the upper left.\r\n\r\nThe site will be live soon!','Photographer Website','','inherit','open','open','','158-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:17:34','2013-07-14 23:17:34','',158,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/158-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(325,1,'2013-07-12 17:12:24','2013-07-12 23:12:24','<a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ski_design1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-71\" alt=\"ski_design1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ski_design1.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"1000\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-75\" alt=\"Ski Design 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ski_design2.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012 – 2013\r\n\r\nI\'ve recently been working with Kelvin Wu, a fellow resident of Jackson Hole who builds custom skis from scratch. Please visit his website at <a href=\"http://skibuilders.com/\" target=\"_blank\">skibuilders.com</a> if you\'d like to see his side of the creative and manufacturing process of ski design, or if you\'ve ever wanted to own that pair of skis custom-made just for you.\r\n\r\nDesigning graphics for skis has always been a fantasy of mine (one of the reasons I got into the design industry in the first place), so this opportunity has been like a dream come true. I hope to continue adding to the gallery above as we produce new designs and skis in the days to come.\r\n\r\nDesigning for skis offers a challenge—the long, skinny format, blending the design between the two skis—that makes designing them beyond fun. And I can\'t wait to see a pair in use.','Ski Graphics','','inherit','open','open','','70-revision-v1','','','2013-07-12 17:12:24','2013-07-12 23:12:24','',70,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/12/70-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(326,1,'2013-07-14 17:17:23','2013-07-14 23:17:23','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-163\" alt=\"UM Environmental Studies\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/evst_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"840\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Web Design / Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Fireworks, Illustrator, Dreamweaver\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a website I designed and developed for The University of Montana Environmental Studies program.\r\n\r\nI also designed the Environmental Studies logo, header graphic, and PEAS Farm and Camas Magazine icons to go with the website.\r\n\r\nYou can view the site live at <a href=\"http://www.cas.umt.edu/evst/\" target=\"_blank\">www.cas.umt.edu/evst</a>.','UM Environmental Studies Website','','inherit','open','open','','162-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:17:23','2013-07-14 23:17:23','',162,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/162-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(327,1,'2013-07-12 17:12:55','2013-07-12 23:12:55','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-66\" alt=\"Umbrella Typogram\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/umbrella_typogram_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"483\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-62\" alt=\"Through Thick &amp; Thin Typogram\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/thick_thin_typogram_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"364\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-60\" alt=\"Polkadot Typogram\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/polkadot_typogram_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"720\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-61\" alt=\"Streetlight Typogram\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/streetlight_typogram_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"675\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nTypogram: a word that, through the manipulation of the letterform itself, illustrates the meaning of the word.\r\n\r\nThis is a series of typograms I designed and created for a university typography class. I also included my pencil and paper concept sketches.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" style=\"float: left;\" alt=\"Typogram Sketches 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/typogram_sketches1.jpg\" width=\"50%\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65\" style=\"float: left;\" alt=\"Typogram Sketches 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/typogram_sketches2.jpg\" width=\"50%\" />','Typograms','','inherit','open','open','','58-revision-v1','','','2013-07-12 17:12:55','2013-07-12 23:12:55','',58,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/12/58-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(328,1,'2013-07-14 17:17:14','2013-07-14 23:17:14','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/30769977?color=c9ff23\" width=\"900\" height=\"507\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe> <p><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/30769977\">Flyaway Dreams</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<b>Category:</b> Animation\r\n<b>Created Using:</b> Toon Boom Animate, Photoshop, After Effects, Wacom Tablet\r\n<b>Date:</b> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a hand-drawn, frame-by-frame animation. In this story, the character finds an umbrella, gets blown into the sky, floats all day, falls asleep, drifts back to the ground, wakes up, and wonders what the whole thing was about – he shrugs it off as a dream and walks away. Feel free to come up with your own interpretation!','Flyaway Dreams','','inherit','open','open','','166-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:17:14','2013-07-14 23:17:14','',166,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/166-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(329,1,'2013-07-14 17:15:31','2013-07-14 23:15:31','<h2>Orange</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233\" alt=\"Orange\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/orange_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nSpringtime bison calf in Yellowstone National Park.\r\n<h2>Exoskeleton</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-226\" alt=\"Exoskeleton\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/exoskeleton_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nFound this little guy (or what was once this little guy, anyway) while enjoying a winter hot springs adventure.\r\n<h2>Hang Time</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227\" alt=\"Hang Time\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/hang_time_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI love frogs! Taken at the Chattanooga Aquarium while on a college marching band trip.\r\n<h2>Look at Me</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228\" alt=\"Look at Me\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/look_at_me_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nIs it ok for birds to stand in and eat/drink out of a geyser? I don\'t honestly know.\r\n<h2>Calvin</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" alt=\"Calvin\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/calvin_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"465\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nThis is one of my cats, Calvin. He can be quite photogenic when he wants to be.','Animal Photography','','inherit','open','open','','222-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:15:31','2013-07-14 23:15:31','',222,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/222-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(330,1,'2013-07-14 17:18:53','2013-07-14 23:18:53','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/16623351?color=cdda57\" height=\"491\" width=\"872\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/16623351\" target=\"_blank\">Overgrown</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Paper, Chair, Lamp, Photoshop, Final Cut, Logic\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is an experimental stop motion animation I did for my University of Montana Media Arts animation class.\r\n\r\nIt consists of dozens of little creepy tree paper cutouts that I taped to a chair, lit with a lamp, and then photographed the shadows. I used a replacement animation technique. I made the title by cutting out the words from a piece of paper, holding it up to a light, taking the picture, then inverting the black and white.\r\n\r\nI wanted to experiment with different shadows to create a unique, abstract stop motion animation. The soundtrack is a custom sound design piece I created in Logic.\r\n<h2>Trees</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-119\" alt=\"Overgrown Trees\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/overgrown_trees.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n<h2>Storyboards</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-117\" alt=\"Overgrown Storyboards\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/overgrown_storyboards.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"673\" />\r\n<h2>Tree &amp; Animation Setup Concepts</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-118\" alt=\"Overgrown Tree Concepts\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/overgrown_tree_concepts.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />','Overgrown','','inherit','open','open','','116-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:18:53','2013-07-14 23:18:53','',116,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/116-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(331,1,'2013-07-14 17:15:16','2013-07-14 23:15:16','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-293\" alt=\"Brew &amp; View\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/brew_and_view_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"582\" height=\"900\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nDesigned for Sapore Restaurant &amp; Bar in Missoula, Montana for their weekly pizza, beer and a movie event.\r\n\r\nThis poster was used through the winter and ski season, so has a winter theme.\r\n\r\nI designed the concept, layout and graphics for the poster.','Brew & View','','inherit','open','open','','291-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:15:16','2013-07-14 23:15:16','',291,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/291-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(332,1,'2013-07-14 17:19:09','2013-07-14 23:19:09','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/15644555?color=cdda57\" height=\"470\" width=\"752\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/15644555\" target=\"_blank\">Bounce</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Index Cards, Pencil &amp; Sharpie, Scanner, Final Cut\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a flip book I made for my University of Montana Media Arts animation class.\r\n\r\nI first drew out 128 pictures on index cards, outlined then in Sharpie, scanned them in one by one (which took a LONG time), and finally edited them together and added audio in Final Cut.\r\n<h2>Card Stack</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-112\" alt=\"Bounce Card Stack\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bounce_card_stack.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />\r\n<h2>Cards Example</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-113\" alt=\"Bounce Cards Example\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bounce_cards.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />','Bounce','','inherit','open','open','','111-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:19:09','2013-07-14 23:19:09','',111,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/111-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(333,1,'2013-07-14 17:16:29','2013-07-14 23:16:29','<h2>Wedding Reflection</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-194\" alt=\"Wedding Reflection\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/wedding_reflection_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nI took this photo while photographing a friend\'s Christmas Eve wedding. So much fun!\r\n<h2>Foot Friends</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-191\" alt=\"Foot Friends\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/foot_friends_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"465\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nFun in the sun at Flathead Lake, Montana. I didn\'t realize I was so tan...\r\n<h2>Mirrored Horizon</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-192\" alt=\"Mirrored Horizon\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/mirrored_horizon_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAn interesting perspective on Jenny Lake in Grand Teton National Park.\r\n<h2>Contemplative</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-190\" alt=\"Contemplative\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/contemplative_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nStrolling along the shore of Yellowstone Lake\r\n<h2>Circle of Friends</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-189\" alt=\"Circle of Friends\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circle_of_friends_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nA circle of friends.\r\n<h2>White Winter</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-195\" alt=\"White Winter\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/white_winter_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nEnjoying a cross-country ski in a snowstorm.\r\n<h2>Mountaintop</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-193\" alt=\"Mountaintop\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/mountaintop_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nTaken atop a mountain surrounding Jackson Hole, WY at sunset.','People Photography','','inherit','open','open','','188-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:16:29','2013-07-14 23:16:29','',188,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/188-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(334,1,'2013-07-14 17:19:24','2013-07-14 23:19:24','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/15852498?color=cdda57\" height=\"471\" width=\"856\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/15852498\" target=\"_blank\">A Simple Gift</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, Final Cut\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a fun little animation I did for a Media Arts animation class. I made it by saving 227 individual jpegs out of a Photoshop document I created and then editing them together and adding audio in Final Cut. It\'s essentially a digital flipbook.\r\n\r\nThe music is Kate Nash\'s \"Merry Happy.\"\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Frame Sequence Demonstration</h2>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-92\" alt=\"A Simple Gift Frames Demonstration\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/a_simple_gift_frames_demonstration.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"333\" />\r\n\r\nHere is a sample of three frames, each consisting of a separate jpeg, from three different scenes.','A Simple Gift','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:19:24','2013-07-14 23:19:24','',86,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/86-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(335,1,'2013-07-14 17:17:04','2013-07-14 23:17:04','<h2>Elemental</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-181\" alt=\"Elemental\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/elemental_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nSpring in Yellowstone\'s Grand Canyon. Where Earth, Water, Fire and Air meet.\r\n<h2>Edge</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-225\" alt=\"Edge\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/edge_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nAt the Sulfur Pot in Yellowstone, stench doesn\'t effect beauty.\r\n<h2>Radiance of a Tree</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-182\" alt=\"Radiance of a Tree\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/radiance_of_a_tree_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"465\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nTrees in autumn know how to do it right. We may try to capture they\'re beauty, and maybe sometimes we succeed, but it seems nature usually gives us the one-up.\r\n<h2>Where Earth Meets Sky</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-184\" alt=\"Where Earth Meets Sky\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/where_earth_meets_sky_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"387\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nThe Teton Range during a dramatic sunset. I was lucky to catch this sight while on a walk up the butte near my home.\r\n<h2>Dewdrops</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-180\" alt=\"Dewdrops\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/dewdrops_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nGetting up for the sunrise while camping is always well worth it. In my opinion, nothing surpasses nature in the early morning.\r\n<h2>Barren</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179\" alt=\"Barren\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/barren_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nNatural beauty at its best.\r\n<h2>Reaching</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-183\" alt=\"Reaching\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/reaching_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nSpring moss reaching for the sun above its snow-covered log in early spring.\r\n<h2>Diversity</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-185\" alt=\"Diversity\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/diversity_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nHow many different kinds of moss and lichen can fit on one small twig?','Nature Photography','','inherit','open','open','','178-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:17:04','2013-07-14 23:17:04','',178,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/178-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(336,1,'2013-07-14 17:19:40','2013-07-14 23:19:40','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-83\" alt=\"Typography Poster\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/typography_poster_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"485\" height=\"749\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nThis is an informational poster I made for a fake event as part of a university typography class.\r\n\r\nWe could only use simple graphical elements: the main concentration was supposed to be on letterform and manipulating the layout of text on the page to create something interesting.\r\n\r\nThis piece are not tied to any of the real organizations portrayed on the posters in any way.','Typography Poster','','inherit','open','open','','82-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:19:40','2013-07-14 23:19:40','',82,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/82-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(337,1,'2013-07-14 17:18:33','2013-07-14 23:18:33','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/29126262?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/29126262\" target=\"_blank\">Logo Build</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> After Effects, Illustrator\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a logo build I animated for one of my university After Effects classes. I didn\'t design the logo, but recreated it in Illustrator and later animated it in After Effects.\r\n\r\n*This piece has no tie to the company Clean Conscience LTD and is not approved or supported by them.','Logo Build','','inherit','open','open','','125-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:18:33','2013-07-14 23:18:33','',125,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/125-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(338,1,'2013-07-14 17:17:00','2013-07-14 23:17:00','<h2>Rusalka: The Little Mermaid Story – Set Backdrop Motion Design Videos</h2>\r\nThis is one of 16 videos I made for the University of British Columbia\'s production of Antonín Dvorák\'s opera Rusalka: The Little Mermaid Story, February 9-12, 2012. The videos were projected onto the back of the set behind the stage. I made them in After Effects, using various effects and particles.\r\n\r\nHere\'s one of the videos, shortened a bit:\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/38334568?color=c9ff23\" height=\"675\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/38334568\">Rusalka Opera, University of British Colombia, Set Projection Video</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.\r\n<strong>Categories:</strong> Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, After Effects\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nHere\'s the program (which I didn\'t design, but am credited as \"Ali Gray: Motion Graphic Artist\" on page 3):\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-172\" alt=\"Rusalka Program 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rusalka_program_cover_small.jpg\" width=\"388\" height=\"613\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-173\" alt=\"Ruslaka Program 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rusalka_program_pg1_small_900.jpg\" width=\"785\" height=\"609\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-174\" alt=\"Rusalka Program 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rusalka_program_pg2_small_ali_gray_900.jpg\" width=\"785\" height=\"610\" />\r\n\r\n*Note: I did not photograph the image in the video above nor do I own it or any right to it. It was simply given to me by the client to use for the videos. Also, I did not design any part of this program, nor own any rights to it.\r\n\r\nFor more information on the opera, please view this article: <a href=\"http://wire.arts.ubc.ca/events/rusalka-the-little-mermaid-story/\" target=\"_blank\">http://wire.arts.ubc.ca/events/rusalka-the-little-mermaid-story/</a> (the \"state of the art projection technology\" mentioned refers to these videos).','Rusalka','','inherit','open','open','','171-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:17:00','2013-07-14 23:17:00','',171,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/171-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(339,1,'2013-07-14 17:18:24','2013-07-14 23:18:24','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/41753612?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/41753612\" target=\"_blank\">Concentric</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Motion Design / 3D\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Cinema 4D, After Effects\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nThis was my last project for UM Media Arts, but done for an after-the-fact special topics 3D Animation class. It\'s based on the awesome video Spherikal (<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/39792837\" target=\"_blank\">vimeo.com/39792837</a>), which I did following GreyScaleGorilla\'s tutorial (<a href=\"http://greyscalegorilla.com/blog/2012/04/clones-step-effector-and-atom-array-tutorial-for-cinema-4d/\" target=\"_blank\">greyscalegorilla.com/blog/2012/04/clones-step-effector-and-atom-array-tutorial-for-cinema-4d/</a>), with a few touches of my own.\r\n\r\nMusic: \"The Sun is Scheduled to Come out Tomorrow\" by Chris Zabriskie (<a href=\"http://chriszabriskie.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chriszabriskie.com</a>).','Concentric','','inherit','open','open','','127-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:18:24','2013-07-14 23:18:24','',127,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/127-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(340,1,'2013-07-14 17:17:58','2013-07-14 23:17:58','*Move your mouse to draw, and click and hold your mouse button to change the color!\r\n*It may take a moment to load.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://dl.dropbox.com/u/44105561/basic_interactivity2/applet/index.html\" height=\"664\" width=\"660\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Processing / Interactive / Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Processing\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nI made this interactive piece using <a href=\"http://processing.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Processing</a>, an open-source programming language and environment for people who want to create images, animations and interactions.\r\n\r\nHere are some examples of screenshots I took after playing with my Processing applet:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-143\" alt=\"Processing 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing1.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-148\" alt=\"Processing 6\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing6.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-147\" alt=\"Processing 5\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing5.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-144\" alt=\"Processing 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing2.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-146\" alt=\"Processing 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing4.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-145\" alt=\"Processing 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing3.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />','Build it Up','','inherit','open','open','','142-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:17:58','2013-07-14 23:17:58','',142,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/142-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(341,1,'2013-07-14 17:15:47','2013-07-14 23:15:47','<h2>Teeth</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-214\" alt=\"Teeth\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/teeth_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nI took this photo at my parents\' house. There is an awesome vintage saw hanging on the side of the log garage, and I couldn\'t resist photographing its gnarly teeth and their sharp contrast against the circular tree rings.\r\n<h2>Oxidized</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-211\" alt=\"Oxidized\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/oxidized_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"465\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo at Flathead Lake in Montana. There was an old boat shack on the shore that was rusted and weathered in an amazing way, perfect for a photo.\r\n<h2>Winter Cycle</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-215\" alt=\"Winter Cycle\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/winter_cycle_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nPart of the rope tow at the top of Lost Trail Powder Mountain ski area in Montana/Idaho. Loved the orange.\r\n<h2>Doorway</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-224\" alt=\"Doorway\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doorway_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nAmazing door to one of the rooms at the Old Faithful Inn in Yellowstone.\r\n<h2>Sail Away</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213\" alt=\"Sail Away\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sail_away_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nTaken while sailing on Jackson Lake in Grand Teton National Park. Went a little overboard with Photoshop, but I think the abstract-ness of the photo called for it.\r\n<h2>Color Wheel</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-208\" alt=\"Color Wheel\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circular_color_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nThis crayon tower had such amazing colors! Boosting said colors beyond the natural is always fun, as well.\r\n<h2>Nature\'s Symmetry</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-210\" alt=\"Nature\'s Symmetry\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/natures_symmetry_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nNature has such a knack for creating beauty everywhere you look.\r\n<h2>Pathways</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-212\" alt=\"Pathways\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/pathways_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nCan you guess what this is? It\'s actually a quilt, somehow transformed into a very three-dimensional looking image.\r\n<h2>Corrugated</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-209\" alt=\"Corrugated\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/corrugated_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nPart of a Missoula river trail underpass—from an ant\'s perspective, anyway.','Industrial & Abstract Photography','','inherit','open','open','','207-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:15:47','2013-07-14 23:15:47','',207,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/207-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(342,1,'2013-07-14 17:18:43','2013-07-14 23:18:43','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/32268385?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/32268385\" target=\"_blank\">Title Sequence</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation / Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects, Logic\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a fake title sequence I designed and animated for an After Effects class. The only real person credited in the title sequence is me, and I made up the film and film name, as well.\r\n\r\nIn creating this piece, I was going for something fun, colorful, jazzy, and full of animation.\r\n\r\nThe music is \"Rythme Gitan\" by Latché Swing <a href=\"http://www.jamendo.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">(jamendo.com/en/artist/latche_swing_(3))</a>.\r\n<h2>Storyboards</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-123\" alt=\"Title Sequence Storyboards\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/title_sequence_storyboards.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"334\" />','Title Sequence','','inherit','open','open','','122-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:18:43','2013-07-14 23:18:43','',122,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/122-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(343,1,'2013-07-14 17:17:46','2013-07-14 23:17:46','<h2>Perspective View 1</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-154\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_persp_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n<h2>Perspective View 2</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_persp3_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n<h2>Front View</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-153\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_front_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n<h2>Rear View</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-152\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_buckle_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> 3D Modeling &amp; Texturing\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Maya\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThese goggles were the first thing I ever spent any recognizable amount of time building in 3D. Now I just need to find the time to use them in an animation...','Steampunk Goggles','','inherit','open','open','','151-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:17:46','2013-07-14 23:17:46','',151,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/151-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(344,1,'2013-07-14 17:16:17','2013-07-14 23:16:17','<h2>Drip, Drip, Drip</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-202\" alt=\"Drip Drip Drip\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/drip_drip_drip_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo as part of a photography assignment for a university class, in which we had to find or create interesting text and letterforms and photograph them. I created and lit this scene in order to accomplish the look and concept I was after.\r\n<h2>China Shipping</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-200\" alt=\"China Shipping\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/china_shipping_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"574\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nWhile out scouting for interesting typography and text to photograph for a typography class, I suddenly happened upon this fantastic truck parked in a downtown Missoula parking lot. What a great find!\r\n<h2>The Color of Rust</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" alt=\"The Color of Rust\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/the_color_of_rust_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nIt\'s amazing what you can find among a bunch of old rusty mining equipment in the middle of an old field in the industrial sector of a Montana town.\r\n<h2>Million Dollar</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" alt=\"Million Dollar\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/million_dollar_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAs I currently live in Jackson Hole, WY, I figured I might as well take a picture of the famous bar every one of the thousands of tourists take pictures of every day—but in a different way.\r\n<h2>Doble V</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-201\" alt=\"Doble V\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doble_v_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nFinding the right crop is what turning a boring apartment complex sign into something unique is all about.\r\n<h2>Symmetry</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-204\" alt=\"Symmetry\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/symmetry_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"629\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAnother interesting find for my typography photography assignment. Loved the symmetrical and asymmetrical aspects of the inside of this gazebo roof.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Text Photography','','inherit','open','open','','199-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 17:16:17','2013-07-14 23:16:17','',199,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/199-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(353,1,'2013-07-12 11:00:18','2013-07-12 17:00:18','*I claim no rights to any of the designs on this page. All designs and content belong to <a href=\"http://www.circ.biz/\" target=\"_blank\">Circ</a>.\r\n<h2>Business Collateral</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-363\" alt=\"Circ Business Collateral, graphic design\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-business-collateral.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"506\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-366\" alt=\"Circ Notecard\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-notecard.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"643\" />\r\n\r\n[one_half]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-365\" alt=\"Circ Notecard Back\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-notecard-back.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"294\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-362\" alt=\"Circ Business Card Back\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-business-card-back.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"294\" />\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design</h2>\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> InDesign\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nThe business collateral I designed for <a href=\"http://www.circ.biz/\" target=\"_blank\">Circ</a> consists of business cards, notecards and two types of address label stickers. A unique aspect of the design is the use of spot UV varnish for the background speech bubbles, which 