ignnone size-full wp-image-360\" alt=\"Circ Building Sign Back\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ_building_side_sign.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"214\" />\r\n[/one_half_last]','Circ: Graphic Design','','inherit','open','open','','353-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 13:20:10','2013-07-16 19:20:10','',353,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/353-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(381,1,'2013-07-14 19:09:45','2013-07-15 01:09:45','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-159\" alt=\"Photographer Website\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photographer_website_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Web Design / Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nThis is a website I designed for a talented photographer in the Missoula area. She has asked to remain anonymous until the site goes live, so that is the reason for the large white circle in the upper left.\r\n\r\nThe site will be live soon!','Photographer Website','','inherit','open','open','','158-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 19:09:45','2013-07-15 01:09:45','',158,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/158-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(382,1,'2013-07-14 19:14:30','2013-07-15 01:14:30','<h2>Teeth</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-214\" alt=\"Teeth\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/teeth_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nI took this photo at my parents\' house. There is an awesome vintage saw hanging on the side of the log garage, and I couldn\'t resist photographing its gnarly teeth and their sharp contrast against the circular tree rings.\r\n<h2>Oxidized</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-211\" alt=\"Oxidized\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/oxidized_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"465\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo at Flathead Lake in Montana. There was an old boat shack on the shore that was rusted and weathered in an amazing way, perfect for a photo.\r\n<h2>Winter Cycle</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-215\" alt=\"Winter Cycle\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/winter_cycle_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nPart of the rope tow at the top of Lost Trail Powder Mountain ski area in Montana/Idaho. Loved the orange.\r\n<h2>Doorway</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-224\" alt=\"Doorway\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doorway_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nAmazing door to one of the rooms at the Old Faithful Inn in Yellowstone.\r\n<h2>Sail Away</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213\" alt=\"Sail Away\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sail_away_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nTaken while sailing on Jackson Lake in Grand Teton National Park. Went a little overboard with Photoshop, but I think the abstract-ness of the photo called for it.\r\n<h2>Color Wheel</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-208\" alt=\"Color Wheel\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circular_color_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nThis crayon tower had such amazing colors! Boosting said colors beyond the natural is always fun, as well.\r\n<h2>Nature\'s Symmetry</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-210\" alt=\"Nature\'s Symmetry\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/natures_symmetry_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nNature has such a knack for creating beauty everywhere you look.\r\n<h2>Pathways</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-212\" alt=\"Pathways\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/pathways_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nCan you guess what this is? It\'s actually a quilt, somehow transformed into a very three-dimensional looking image.\r\n<h2>Corrugated</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-209\" alt=\"Corrugated\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/corrugated_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nPart of a Missoula river trail underpass—from an ant\'s perspective, anyway.','Industrial & Abstract Photography','','inherit','open','open','','207-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 19:14:30','2013-07-15 01:14:30','',207,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/207-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(383,1,'2014-07-06 12:15:27','2014-07-06 18:15:27','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/32268385?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/32268385\" target=\"_blank\">Title Sequence</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n<h2 class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Category:</strong> Animation / Motion Design</h2>\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects, Logic\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\n\nGetting into motion design and animation in college, I wanted to create a title sequence from the start. With this piece for an After Effects class, I finally had the opportunity! Although at the time I didn\'t have a friend shooting a film, and I find recreating things that have already been done a bit cliche, a fake title sequence was in order. The only real person credited in the title sequence is me, and I made up the film and film name, as well.\n\nIn creating this piece, I was going for something fun, colorful, jazzy, and full of animation.\n\nThe music is \"Rythme Gitan\" by Latché Swing <a href=\"http://www.jamendo.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">(jamendo.com/en/artist/latche_swing_(3))</a>.\n<h2>Storyboards</h2>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-123\" alt=\"Title Sequence Storyboards, motion design\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/title_sequence_storyboards.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"334\" />','Title Sequence','Title sequence for a fictional film which features geometric shapes, fun colors and jazzy music.','inherit','open','open','','122-autosave-v1','','','2014-07-06 12:15:27','2014-07-06 18:15:27','',122,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/122-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(384,1,'2013-07-14 19:14:56','2013-07-15 01:14:56','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/32268385?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/32268385\" target=\"_blank\">Title Sequence</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation / Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects, Logic\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a fake title sequence I designed and animated for an After Effects class. The only real person credited in the title sequence is me, and I made up the film and film name, as well.\r\n\r\nIn creating this piece, I was going for something fun, colorful, jazzy, and full of animation.\r\n\r\nThe music is \"Rythme Gitan\" by Latché Swing <a href=\"http://www.jamendo.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">(jamendo.com/en/artist/latche_swing_(3))</a>.\r\n<h2>Storyboards</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-123\" alt=\"Title Sequence Storyboards\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/title_sequence_storyboards.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"334\" />','Title Sequence','','inherit','open','open','','122-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 19:14:56','2013-07-15 01:14:56','',122,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/122-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(385,1,'2013-07-16 13:32:38','2013-07-16 19:32:38','<h2>Business Collateral</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-363\" alt=\"Circ Business Collateral\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-business-collateral.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"506\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-366\" alt=\"Circ Notecard\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-notecard.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"643\" />\r\n\r\n[one_half]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-365\" alt=\"Circ Notecard Back\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-notecard-back.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"294\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-362\" alt=\"Circ Business Card Back\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-business-card-back.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"294\" />\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n<h2>Facebook Branding</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-364\" alt=\"Circ Facebook\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-facebook.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"433\" />\r\n<h2>Company Values</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-367\" alt=\"Circ Values\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ-values.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"900\" />\r\n<h2>Portfolio Brochure</h2>\r\n[one_half]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-355\" alt=\"Circ Brochure 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ_brochure-1.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"232\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-356\" alt=\"Circ Brochure 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ_brochure-2.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"232\" />\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\n[one_half]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-357\" alt=\"Circ Brochure 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ_brochure-3.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"232\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-358\" alt=\"Circ Brochure 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ_brochure-4.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"232\" />\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n<h2>Conference Room Desktop</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-361\" alt=\"Circ C Desktop Dig Deeper\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ_c_desktop_dig_deeper.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"531\" />\r\n<h2>Building Signage</h2>\r\n[one_half]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-359\" alt=\"Circ Building Sign Front\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ_building_front_sign.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"214\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-360\" alt=\"Circ Building Sign Back\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circ_building_side_sign.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"214\" />\r\n[/one_half_last]','Circ: Graphic Design','Features business collateral, advertising material pieces, a desktop wallpaper, and exterior signage mockups for Circ in Jackson, WY.','inherit','open','open','','353-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 13:32:38','2013-07-16 19:32:38','',353,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/353-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(386,1,'2013-07-16 13:29:54','2013-07-16 19:29:54','<a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ski_design1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-71\" alt=\"ski_design1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ski_design1.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"1000\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-75\" alt=\"Ski Design 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ski_design2.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012 – 2013\r\n\r\nI\'ve recently been working with Kelvin Wu, a fellow resident of Jackson Hole who builds custom skis from scratch. Please visit his website at <a href=\"http://skibuilders.com/\" target=\"_blank\">skibuilders.com</a> if you\'d like to see his side of the creative and manufacturing process of ski design, or if you\'ve ever wanted to own that pair of skis custom-made just for you.\r\n\r\nDesigning graphics for skis has always been a fantasy of mine (one of the reasons I got into the design industry in the first place), so this opportunity has been like a dream come true. I hope to continue adding to the gallery above as we produce new designs and skis in the days to come.\r\n\r\nDesigning for skis offers a challenge—the long, skinny format, blending the design between the two skis—that makes designing them beyond fun. And I can\'t wait to see a pair in use.','Ski Graphics','Top graphics created for a custom ski manufacturer in Jackson, WY.','inherit','open','open','','70-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 13:29:54','2013-07-16 19:29:54','',70,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/70-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(387,1,'2013-07-16 13:30:54','2013-07-16 19:30:54','This was a digital art installation presented for the First Friday Art Walk in downtown Missoula, Montana. It was a collaboration between my fellow University of Montana Media Arts students Lindy Jones, Sari Jones, Preston Schulz, Chelsey Von Ehrenkrook, and myself (aka \"The Dream Team\").\r\n<h2>Vertical Projection, Large Stacked Boxes, Lantern with Spotlight</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-130\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption1.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Stacked Boxes with Spotlight and LED Lightstrip</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-131\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption2.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Main Projection Animation</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-132\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption3.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" />\r\n<h2>Stacked Boxes with LED Lightstrip, Lantern with Spotlight, Bar</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-133\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption4.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Televisions with Animations, Lantern with Spotlight</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-134\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 5\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption5.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Televisions, Lantern with Spotlight, Vertical Projection, Stacked Boxes</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-135\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 6\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption6.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"502\" />\r\n<h2>Small Stacked Boxes</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-138\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption 9\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption9.jpg\" width=\"464\" height=\"696\" />\r\n<h2>\"The Dream Team\"</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-136\" alt=\"The Dream Team\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption7.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" />\r\n<h2>Advertising Poster</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-137\" alt=\"The Bad Contraption Poster\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bad_contraption8.jpg\" width=\"464\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2>Main Animation Projection</h2>\r\nThe animation is 10 1/2 minutes long, but feel free to scrub through it! Some of the pizzaz of the original color was lost in the compression. :(\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/24902526?color=cdda57\" height=\"531\" width=\"720\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/24902526\" target=\"_blank\">The Bad Contraption: Main Video</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vertical Animation Projection</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/24901626?color=cdda57\" height=\"400\" width=\"226\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/24901626\" target=\"_blank\">The Bad Contraption: Particles</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Installation Video</h2>\r\nThe spotlights on the wall behind the boxes and on the giant paper lanterns weren\'t up yet, so the video is dark, less colorful and doesn\'t look like the finished product. :(\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/18094025?color=cdda57\" height=\"366\" width=\"650\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/18094025\" target=\"_blank\">The Bad Contraption</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Digital Art Installation / Motion Design / Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, After Effects, LED spotlights &amp; lightstrips, paper lanterns, boxes, duct tape, paper, TVs, projectors\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nOur goal for The Bad Contraption was to create a space in which people could get lost; a surreal, topsy-turvy world.\r\n\r\nIt consisted of two animations projected onto the walls, large stacks of boxes with patterns taped onto them stacked around the room, colored LED lightstrips and spotlights, huge hanging paper lanterns, five televisions which also showed the animations, and piles upon piles of small pink and white boxes viewers could interact and play with. It was held at the Badlander Bar.\r\n\r\nPhoto credits: Jesse Spaulding, Sari Jones, and Ali Gray. Animation Video Credits: The Dream Team. Video credit: Jesse Spaulding.','The Bad Contraption','Digital art installation for the Missoula First Friday Art Walk. Features motion design projections, interactive props, and lighting.','inherit','open','open','','129-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 13:30:54','2013-07-16 19:30:54','',129,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/129-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(388,1,'2013-07-16 13:36:59','2013-07-16 19:36:59','<a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ski_design1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-71\" alt=\"ski_design1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ski_design1.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"1000\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-75\" alt=\"Ski Design 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ski_design2.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012 – 2013\r\n\r\nI\'ve recently been working with Kelvin Wu, a fellow resident of Jackson Hole who builds custom skis from scratch. Please visit his website at <a href=\"http://skibuilders.com/\" target=\"_blank\">skibuilders.com</a> if you\'d like to see his side of the creative and manufacturing process of ski design, or if you\'ve ever wanted to own that pair of skis custom-made just for you.\r\n\r\nDesigning graphics for skis has always been a fantasy of mine (one of the reasons I got into the design industry in the first place), so this opportunity has been like a dream come true. I hope to continue adding to the gallery above as we produce new designs and skis in the days to come.\r\n\r\nDesigning for skis offers a challenge—the long, skinny format, blending the design between the two skis—that makes designing them beyond fun. And I can\'t wait to see a pair in use.','Ski Graphics','A collection of graphics created for a custom ski manufacturer in Jackson, WY.','inherit','open','open','','70-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 13:36:59','2013-07-16 19:36:59','',70,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/70-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(389,1,'2013-07-16 13:33:40','2013-07-16 19:33:40','<h2>Teeth</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-214\" alt=\"Teeth\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/teeth_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nI took this photo at my parents\' house. There is an awesome vintage saw hanging on the side of the log garage, and I couldn\'t resist photographing its gnarly teeth and their sharp contrast against the circular tree rings.\r\n<h2>Oxidized</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-211\" alt=\"Oxidized\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/oxidized_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"465\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo at Flathead Lake in Montana. There was an old boat shack on the shore that was rusted and weathered in an amazing way, perfect for a photo.\r\n<h2>Winter Cycle</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-215\" alt=\"Winter Cycle\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/winter_cycle_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nPart of the rope tow at the top of Lost Trail Powder Mountain ski area in Montana/Idaho. Loved the orange.\r\n<h2>Doorway</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-224\" alt=\"Doorway\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doorway_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nAmazing door to one of the rooms at the Old Faithful Inn in Yellowstone.\r\n<h2>Sail Away</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213\" alt=\"Sail Away\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sail_away_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nTaken while sailing on Jackson Lake in Grand Teton National Park. Went a little overboard with Photoshop, but I think the abstract-ness of the photo called for it.\r\n<h2>Color Wheel</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-208\" alt=\"Color Wheel\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circular_color_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nThis crayon tower had such amazing colors! Boosting said colors beyond the natural is always fun, as well.\r\n<h2>Nature\'s Symmetry</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-210\" alt=\"Nature\'s Symmetry\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/natures_symmetry_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nNature has such a knack for creating beauty everywhere you look.\r\n<h2>Pathways</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-212\" alt=\"Pathways\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/pathways_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nCan you guess what this is? It\'s actually a quilt, somehow transformed into a very three-dimensional looking image.\r\n<h2>Corrugated</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-209\" alt=\"Corrugated\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/corrugated_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nPart of a Missoula river trail underpass—from an ant\'s perspective, anyway.','Industrial & Abstract Photography','A collection of my photographs featuring industrial or abstract themes.','inherit','open','open','','207-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 13:33:40','2013-07-16 19:33:40','',207,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/207-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(390,1,'2013-07-16 13:35:37','2013-07-16 19:35:37','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/32268385?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/32268385\" target=\"_blank\">Title Sequence</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation / Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects, Logic\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a fake title sequence I designed and animated for an After Effects class. The only real person credited in the title sequence is me, and I made up the film and film name, as well.\r\n\r\nIn creating this piece, I was going for something fun, colorful, jazzy, and full of animation.\r\n\r\nThe music is \"Rythme Gitan\" by Latché Swing <a href=\"http://www.jamendo.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">(jamendo.com/en/artist/latche_swing_(3))</a>.\r\n<h2>Storyboards</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-123\" alt=\"Title Sequence Storyboards\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/title_sequence_storyboards.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"334\" />','Title Sequence','A title sequence for a fictional film which features geometric shapes, fun colors and jazzy music.','inherit','open','open','','122-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 13:35:37','2013-07-16 19:35:37','',122,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/122-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(391,1,'2013-07-14 19:15:12','2013-07-15 01:15:12','<h2>Perspective View 1</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-154\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_persp_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n<h2>Perspective View 2</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_persp3_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n<h2>Front View</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-153\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_front_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n<h2>Rear View</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-152\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_buckle_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> 3D Modeling &amp; Texturing\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Maya\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThese goggles were the first thing I ever spent any recognizable amount of time building in 3D. Now I just need to find the time to use them in an animation...','Steampunk Goggles','','inherit','open','open','','151-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 19:15:12','2013-07-15 01:15:12','',151,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/151-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(392,1,'2013-07-14 19:15:21','2013-07-15 01:15:21','<h2>Drip, Drip, Drip</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-202\" alt=\"Drip Drip Drip\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/drip_drip_drip_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo as part of a photography assignment for a university class, in which we had to find or create interesting text and letterforms and photograph them. I created and lit this scene in order to accomplish the look and concept I was after.\r\n<h2>China Shipping</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-200\" alt=\"China Shipping\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/china_shipping_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"574\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nWhile out scouting for interesting typography and text to photograph for a typography class, I suddenly happened upon this fantastic truck parked in a downtown Missoula parking lot. What a great find!\r\n<h2>The Color of Rust</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" alt=\"The Color of Rust\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/the_color_of_rust_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nIt\'s amazing what you can find among a bunch of old rusty mining equipment in the middle of an old field in the industrial sector of a Montana town.\r\n<h2>Million Dollar</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" alt=\"Million Dollar\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/million_dollar_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAs I currently live in Jackson Hole, WY, I figured I might as well take a picture of the famous bar every one of the thousands of tourists take pictures of every day—but in a different way.\r\n<h2>Doble V</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-201\" alt=\"Doble V\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doble_v_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nFinding the right crop is what turning a boring apartment complex sign into something unique is all about.\r\n<h2>Symmetry</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-204\" alt=\"Symmetry\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/symmetry_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"629\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAnother interesting find for my typography photography assignment. Loved the symmetrical and asymmetrical aspects of the inside of this gazebo roof.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Text Photography','','inherit','open','open','','199-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 19:15:21','2013-07-15 01:15:21','',199,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/199-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(393,1,'2013-07-14 19:13:22','2013-07-15 01:13:22','*Move your mouse to draw, and click and hold your mouse button to change the color!\r\n*It may take a moment to load.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://dl.dropbox.com/u/44105561/basic_interactivity2/applet/index.html\" height=\"664\" width=\"660\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Processing / Interactive / Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Processing\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nI made this interactive piece using <a href=\"http://processing.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Processing</a>, an open-source programming language and environment for people who want to create images, animations and interactions.\r\n\r\nHere are some examples of screenshots I took after playing with my Processing applet:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-143\" alt=\"Processing 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing1.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-148\" alt=\"Processing 6\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing6.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-147\" alt=\"Processing 5\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing5.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-144\" alt=\"Processing 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing2.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-146\" alt=\"Processing 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing4.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-145\" alt=\"Processing 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/processing3.jpg\" width=\"620\" height=\"620\" />','Build it Up','','inherit','open','open','','142-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 19:13:22','2013-07-15 01:13:22','',142,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/142-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(394,1,'2013-07-14 19:10:46','2013-07-15 01:10:46','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-66\" alt=\"Umbrella Typogram\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/umbrella_typogram_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"483\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-62\" alt=\"Through Thick &amp; Thin Typogram\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/thick_thin_typogram_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"364\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-60\" alt=\"Polkadot Typogram\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/polkadot_typogram_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"720\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-61\" alt=\"Streetlight Typogram\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/streetlight_typogram_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"675\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nTypogram: a word that, through the manipulation of the letterform itself, illustrates the meaning of the word.\r\n\r\nThis is a series of typograms I designed and created for a university typography class. I also included my pencil and paper concept sketches.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" style=\"float: left;\" alt=\"Typogram Sketches 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/typogram_sketches1.jpg\" width=\"50%\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65\" style=\"float: left;\" alt=\"Typogram Sketches 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/typogram_sketches2.jpg\" width=\"50%\" />','Typograms','','inherit','open','open','','58-revision-v1','','','2013-07-14 19:10:46','2013-07-15 01:10:46','',58,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/14/58-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(395,1,'2014-07-06 13:16:33','2014-07-06 19:16:33','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/41753612?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\n\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/41753612\" target=\"_blank\">Concentric</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.\n\n<h2 class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Category:</strong> Motion Design / 3D</h2>\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Cinema 4D, After Effects\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\n\nThis was my last project forUM Media Arts, but done for an after-the-fact special topics 3D Animation class. It\'s based on the awesome video Spherikal (<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/39792837\" target=\"_blank\">vimeo.com/39792837</a>), which I did following GreyScaleGorilla\'s tutorial (<a href=\"http://greyscalegorilla.com/blog/2012/04/clones-step-effector-and-atom-array-tutorial-for-cinema-4d/\" target=\"_blank\">greyscalegorilla.com/blog/2012/04/clones-step-effector-and-atom-array-tutorial-for-cinema-4d/</a>), with a few touches of my own.\n\nMusic: \"The Sun is Scheduled to Come out Tomorrow\" by Chris Zabriskie (<a href=\"http://chriszabriskie.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chriszabriskie.com</a>).','Concentric','Abstract 3D motion design piece.','inherit','open','open','','127-autosave-v1','','','2014-07-06 13:16:33','2014-07-06 19:16:33','',127,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/127-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(396,1,'2013-07-14 19:13:05','2013-07-15 01:13:05','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/41753612?color=cdda57\" height=\"506\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/41753612\" target=\"_blank\">Concentric</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Motion Design / 3D\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Cinema 4D, After Effects\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nThis was my last project for UM Media Arts, but done for an after-the-fact special topics 3D Animation class. It\'s based on the awesome video Spherikal (<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/39792837\" target=\"_blank\">vimeo.com/39792837</a>), which I did following GreyScaleGorilla\'s tutorial (<a href=\"http://greyscalegorilla.com/blog/2012/04/clones-step-effector-and-atom-array-tutorial-