'open','open','','58-revision-v1','','','2013-07-28 17:48:07','2013-07-28 23:48:07','',58,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/28/58-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(483,1,'2013-07-16 14:38:21','2013-07-16 20:38:21','<h2>Rusalka: The Little Mermaid Story – Set Backdrop Motion Design Videos</h2>\r\nThis is one of 16 videos I made for the University of British Columbia\'s production of Antonín Dvorák\'s opera Rusalka: The Little Mermaid Story, February 9-12, 2012. The videos were projected onto the back of the set behind the stage. I made them in After Effects, using various effects and particles.\r\n\r\nHere\'s one of the videos, shortened a bit:\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/38334568?color=c9ff23\" height=\"675\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/38334568\">Rusalka Opera, University of British Colombia, Set Projection Video</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.\r\n<strong>Categories:</strong> Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, After Effects\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nHere\'s the program (which I didn\'t design, but am credited as \"Ali Gray: Motion Graphic Artist\" on page 3):\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-172\" alt=\"Rusalka Program 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rusalka_program_cover_small.jpg\" width=\"388\" height=\"613\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-173\" alt=\"Ruslaka Program 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rusalka_program_pg1_small_900.jpg\" width=\"785\" height=\"609\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-174\" alt=\"Rusalka Program 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rusalka_program_pg2_small_ali_gray_900.jpg\" width=\"785\" height=\"610\" />\r\n\r\n*Note: I did not photograph the image in the video above nor do I own it or any right to it. It was simply given to me by the client to use for the videos. Also, I did not design any part of this program, nor own any rights to it.\r\n\r\nFor more information on the opera, please view this article: <a href=\"http://wire.arts.ubc.ca/events/rusalka-the-little-mermaid-story/\" target=\"_blank\">http://wire.arts.ubc.ca/events/rusalka-the-little-mermaid-story/</a> (the \"state of the art projection technology\" mentioned refers to these videos).','Rusalka','Videos created for the backdrop of an opera put on by the University of British Colombia.','inherit','open','open','','171-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 14:38:21','2013-07-16 20:38:21','',171,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/171-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(484,1,'2013-07-25 17:54:31','2013-07-25 23:54:31','<img class=\"size-full wp-image-50 aligncenter\" alt=\"Wine by Moonlight\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/wine_by_moonlight_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"582\" height=\"900\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator, Photoshop\r\n<strong>Date: </strong>2011\r\n\r\nI designed this poster for Sapore Restaurant and Bar in Missoula, Montana for their weekly wine-tasting event.\r\n\r\nThe goal of the poster was to portray the uniqueness of this particular event, as the tasting room overlooks the rest of downtown Missoula from up on the 3rd story.\r\n\r\nI designed the concept, layout and graphics for the poster.','Wine by Moonlight','Event poster created for a restaurant in Missoula, MT.','inherit','open','open','','19-revision-v1','','','2013-07-25 17:54:31','2013-07-25 23:54:31','',19,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/25/19-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(485,1,'2013-07-28 17:33:19','2013-07-28 23:33:19','<h2>Teeth</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-214\" alt=\"Teeth\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/teeth_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nI took this photo at my parents\' house. There is an awesome vintage saw hanging on the side of the log garage, and I couldn\'t resist photographing its gnarly teeth and their sharp contrast against the circular tree rings.\r\n<h2>Oxidized</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-211\" alt=\"Oxidized\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/oxidized_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"465\" height=\"620\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo at Flathead Lake in Montana. An old, rusty and weathered boat shack on the shore was absolutely perfect for a photo.\r\n<h2>Winter Cycle</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-215\" alt=\"Winter Cycle\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/winter_cycle_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nPart of the rope tow at the top of Lost Trail Powder Mountain ski area in Montana/Idaho. Loved the orange.\r\n<h2>225</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-224\" alt=\"Doorway\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doorway_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nAmazing door to one of the rooms at the Old Faithful Inn in Yellowstone.\r\n<h2>Sail Away</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213\" alt=\"Sail Away\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sail_away_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nTaken while sailing on Jackson Lake in Grand Teton National Park. Went a little overboard with Photoshop, but I think the abstract-ness of the photo called for it.\r\n<h2>Color Wheel</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-208\" alt=\"Color Wheel\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circular_color_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nThis crayon tower had such amazing colors! Boosting said colors beyond the natural is always fun, as well.\r\n<h2>Nature\'s Symmetry</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-210\" alt=\"Nature\'s Symmetry\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/natures_symmetry_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nNature has such a knack for creating beauty everywhere you look.\r\n<h2>Pathways</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-212\" alt=\"Pathways\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/pathways_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nCan you guess what this is? It\'s actually a quilt, transformed into a very three-dimensional looking image.\r\n<h2>Corrugated</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-209\" alt=\"Corrugated\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/corrugated_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nPart of a Missoula river trail underpass—from an ant\'s perspective, anyway.','Industrial & Abstract Photography','Collection of my photographs featuring industrial or abstract themes.','inherit','open','open','','207-revision-v1','','','2013-07-28 17:33:19','2013-07-28 23:33:19','',207,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/28/207-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(486,1,'2013-07-16 13:49:20','2013-07-16 19:49:20','<h2>Perspective View 1</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-154\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_persp_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n<h2>Perspective View 2</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_persp3_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n<h2>Front View</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-153\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_front_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n<h2>Rear View</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-152\" alt=\"Steampunk Goggles 4\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/steampunk_goggles_buckle_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"571\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> 3D Modeling &amp; Texturing\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Maya\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThese goggles were the first thing I ever spent any recognizable amount of time building in 3D. Now I just need to find the time to use them in an animation...','Steampunk Goggles','3D model, complete with lighting and UV texturing.','inherit','open','open','','151-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 13:49:20','2013-07-16 19:49:20','',151,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/151-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(487,1,'2013-07-16 14:40:46','2013-07-16 20:40:46','<h2>Drip, Drip, Drip</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-202\" alt=\"Drip Drip Drip\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/drip_drip_drip_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo as part of a photography assignment for a university class, in which we had to find or create interesting text and letterforms and photograph them. I created and lit this scene in order to accomplish the look and concept I was after.\r\n<h2>China Shipping</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-200\" alt=\"China Shipping\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/china_shipping_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"574\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nWhile out scouting for interesting typography and text to photograph for a typography class, I suddenly happened upon this fantastic truck parked in a downtown Missoula parking lot. What a great find!\r\n<h2>The Color of Rust</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" alt=\"The Color of Rust\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/the_color_of_rust_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nIt\'s amazing what you can find among a bunch of old rusty mining equipment in the middle of an old field in the industrial sector of a Montana town.\r\n<h2>Million Dollar</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" alt=\"Million Dollar\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/million_dollar_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAs I currently live in Jackson Hole, WY, I figured I might as well take a picture of the famous bar every one of the thousands of tourists take pictures of every day—but in a different way.\r\n<h2>Doble V</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-201\" alt=\"Doble V\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doble_v_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nFinding the right crop is what turning a boring apartment complex sign into something unique is all about.\r\n<h2>Symmetry</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-204\" alt=\"Symmetry\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/symmetry_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"629\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Photography\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAnother interesting find for my typography photography assignment. Loved the symmetrical and asymmetrical aspects of the inside of this gazebo roof.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Text Photography','Collection of my photographs featuring text & typography themes.','inherit','open','open','','199-revision-v1','','','2013-07-16 14:40:46','2013-07-16 20:40:46','',199,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/16/199-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(488,1,'2013-07-28 19:16:34','2013-07-29 01:16:34','<h2 class=\"firstH1\">Rusalka: The Little Mermaid Story – Set Backdrop Motion Design Videos</h2>\r\nThis is one of 16 videos I made for the University of British Columbia\'s production of Antonín Dvorák\'s opera Rusalka: The Little Mermaid Story, February 9-12, 2012. The videos were projected onto the back of the set behind the stage. I made them in After Effects, using various effects and particles.\r\n\r\nHere\'s one of the videos, shortened a bit:\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/38334568?color=c9ff23\" height=\"675\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/38334568\">Rusalka Opera, University of British Colombia, Set Projection Video</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.\r\n<strong>Categories:</strong> Motion Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Photoshop, After Effects\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nHere\'s the program (which I didn\'t design, but am credited as \"Ali Gray: Motion Graphic Artist\" on page 3):\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-172\" alt=\"Rusalka Program 1\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rusalka_program_cover_small.jpg\" width=\"388\" height=\"613\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-173\" alt=\"Ruslaka Program 2\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rusalka_program_pg1_small_900.jpg\" width=\"785\" height=\"609\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-174\" alt=\"Rusalka Program 3\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rusalka_program_pg2_small_ali_gray_900.jpg\" width=\"785\" height=\"610\" />\r\n\r\n*Note: I did not photograph the image in the video above nor do I own it or any right to it. It was simply given to me by the client to use for the videos. Also, I did not design any part of this program, nor own any rights to it.\r\n\r\nFor more information on the opera, please view this article: <a href=\"http://wire.arts.ubc.ca/events/rusalka-the-little-mermaid-story/\" target=\"_blank\">http://wire.arts.ubc.ca/events/rusalka-the-little-mermaid-story/</a> (the \"state of the art projection technology\" mentioned refers to these videos).','Rusalka','Videos created for the backdrop of an opera put on by the University of British Colombia.','inherit','open','open','','171-revision-v1','','','2013-07-28 19:16:34','2013-07-29 01:16:34','',171,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/28/171-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(489,1,'2013-07-16 14:40:18','2013-07-16 20:40:18','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-83\" alt=\"Typography Poster\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/typography_poster_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"485\" height=\"749\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Illustrator\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nThis is an informational poster I made for a fake event as part of a university typography class.\r\n\r\nWe could only use simple graphical elements: the main concentration was supposed to be on letterform and manipulating the layout of text on the page to create something interesting.\r\n\r\nThis piece are not tied to any of the real organizations portrayed on the posters in any way.','Typography Poster','Typography event p