ng> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a flip book I made for a university animation class.\r\n\r\nI first drew out 128 pictures on index cards, outlined them in Sharpie, scanned them in one by one (which took a LONG time), and finally edited them together and added audio in Final Cut.\r\n<h2>Card Stack</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-112\" alt=\"Bounce Card Stack\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bounce_card_stack.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />\r\n<h2>Cards Example</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-113\" alt=\"Bounce Cards Example\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/bounce_cards.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" />','Bounce','When our main character is swallowed, escape is just a bounce away in this flip-book animation.','inherit','open','open','','111-revision-v1','','','2013-07-28 20:21:37','2013-07-29 02:21:37','',111,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2013/07/28/111-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(500,1,'2013-07-28 20:27:57','2013-07-29 02:27:57','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/16623351?color=cdda57\" height=\"491\" width=\"872\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p class=\"smaller\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/16623351\" target=\"_blank\">Overgrown</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\" target=\"_blank\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Animation\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Paper, Chair, Lamp, Photoshop, Final Cut, Logic\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a stop motion animation I did for a university animation class.\r\n\r\nIt consists of dozens of little creepy tree paper cutouts that I taped to a chair, lit with a lamp, and then photographed the shadows. I used a replacement animation technique. I made the title by cutting out the words from a piece of paper, holding it up to a light, taking the picture, then inverting the black and white.\r\n\r\nI w