eep and drifts back to the ground. Upon waking up, he wonders what the whole thing was about – and shrugs it off as a dream, walking away. Feel free to come up with your own interpretation!\r\n\r\n<img style=\"display:none;visibility:hidden;\" alt=\"frame-by-frame animation\" />','Flyaway Dreams','What happens if you get whisked away by an umbrella?','inherit','open','open','','166-revision-v1','','','2014-07-06 14:22:07','2014-07-06 20:22:07','',166,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2014/07/06/166-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(699,1,'2014-07-06 14:24:03','2014-07-06 20:24:03','<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/30769977?color=c9ff23\" height=\"507\" width=\"900\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/30769977\">Flyaway Dreams</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/aligray\">Ali Gray</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Category:</strong> Frame-by-Frame Animation</h2>\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Toon Boom Animate, Photoshop, After Effects, Wacom Tablet\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a hand-drawn, frame-by-frame animation. The story all starts with our character finding an innocent umbrella. But when a gust of wind comes up, he gets blown into the sky and floats all day. He eventually falls asleep and drifts back to the ground. Upon waking up, he wonders what the whole thing was about – and shrugs it off as a dream, walking away. Feel free to come up with your own interpretation!\r\n\r\n<img style=\"display:none;visibility:hidden;\" alt=\"frame-by-frame animation\" />','Flyaway Dreams','What happens if you get whisked away by an umbrella?','inherit','open','open','','166-revision-v1','','','2014-07-06 14:24:03','2014-07-06 20:24:03','',166,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2014/07/06/166-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(700,1,'2014-07-06 14:27:27','2014-07-06 20:27:27','*The designs on this page belong to the <a href=\"http://www.umt.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">University of Montana</a> and <a href=\"http://www.cas.umt.edu/sfdesigns/\" target=\"_blank\">Spectral Fusion Designs</a> I apologize if any of the designs have changed or been broken by subsequent updated within each of the respective departments.\r\n<h2>UM Environmental Studies</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-506\" alt=\"Environmental Studies Website, web design\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/evst-ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"574\" />\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Category:</strong> Web Design / Graphic Design</h2>\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Fireworks, Illustrator, Dreamweaver\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nThis is a website I designed and developed for the University of Montana Environmental Studies program. I also designed the Environmental Studies logo and header graphic.\r\n\r\nThe current website has strayed quite a bit from my <a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/evst.jpg\" target=\"_blank\">original design</a> under EVST\'s management, but you can still view it live at <a href=\"http://www.cas.umt.edu/evst/\" target=\"_blank\">www.cas.umt.edu/evst</a>.\r\n<h2>UM Geosciences</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-514\" alt=\"UM Geosciences Website\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/geosciences-ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"574\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Web Design / Graphic Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Fireworks, Illustrator, Dreamweaver, Cascade CMS\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nI designed and developed this website for the University of Montana Department of Geosciences. I had planned on implementing a JQuery slideshow on the homepage, but the Geosciences faculty and staff chose to continue using Picasa. I also designed the footer mountain graphic and EBL, River Center, IFG, and Newsletter icons for the site.\r\n\r\nYou can view the site live at <a href=\"http://www.cas.umt.edu/geosciences/\" target=\"_blank\">www.cas.umt.edu/geosciences</a>, or view the <a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/geosciences_ali_gray.jpg\" target=\"_blank\">full design</a>.\r\n<h2>UM CBSD</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-518\" alt=\"UM CBSD Website\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/cbsd-ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"900\" height=\"574\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Web Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Fireworks, Dreamweaver, Cascade CMS\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nThis is a website I designed and developed for The University of Montana Center for Biomolecular Structure and Dynamics (CBSD).\r\n\r\nYou can view the site live at <a href=\"http://cas.umt.edu/departments/cbsd/\" target=\"_blank\">www.cas.umt.edu/departments/cbsd</a>.\r\n<h2>UM Irish Studies</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-520\" alt=\"UM Irish Studies Website Design\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/irish-studies-ipad-ali-gray.jpg\" width=\"465\" height=\"605\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Web Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Fireworks\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, another design was ultimately chosen, but this was my design for the UM Irish Studies program. I also designed this Irish Studies logo. This design isn\'t associated with UM Irish Studies in any way.\r\n<h2>West Slope Trout Unlimited</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-524\" alt=\"West Slope Trout Unlimited\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/tu-west-slope-ali-gray.jpg\" width=\"605\" height=\"465\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> Web Design\r\n<strong>Created Using:</strong> Fireworks\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAlthough this isn\'t a university website design, I did create it while working as a student web designer at Spectral Fusion Designs. We sometimes designed sites for local non-profits, and this is one example. Another design was ultimately chosen, but I feel this is a good design to showcase here anyway.\r\n\r\n*No part of this design is associated with Trout Unlimited West Slope in any way. All the images are placeholders, and I don\'t claim ownership or own rights to any of the photos.','University Website Designs','Collection of websites I designed and developed for The University of Montana as a student web design worker.','inherit','open','open','','162-revision-v1','','','2014-07-06 14:27:27','2014-07-06 20:27:27','',162,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2014/07/06/162-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(717,1,'2014-07-06 17:10:46','2014-07-06 23:10:46','<h2 class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Category:</strong> Photography</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"firstH1\">Teeth</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/teeth_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Teeth, photography\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-706\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nI took this photo at my parents\' house. There is an awesome vintage saw hanging on the side of the log garage, and I couldn\'t resist photographing its gnarly teeth and their sharp contrast against the circular tree rings.\r\n<h2>Oxidized</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/oxidized_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Oxidized, photography\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-708\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo at Flathead Lake in Montana. An old, rusty and weathered boat shack on the shore was absolutely perfect for a photo.\r\n<h2>Winter Cycle</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/winter_cycle_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Winter Cycle\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-709\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nPart of the rope tow at the top of Lost Trail Powder Mountain ski area in Montana/Idaho. Loved the orange.\r\n<h2>225</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doorway_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Doorway\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-710\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nAmazing door to one of the rooms at the Old Faithful Inn in Yellowstone.\r\n<h2>Sail Away</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sail_away_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Sail Away\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-711\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nTaken while sailing on Jackson Lake in Grand Teton National Park. Went a little overboard with Photoshop, but I think the abstract-ness of the photo called for it.\r\n<h2>Color Wheel</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/circular_color_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Color Wheel\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-712\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nThis crayon tower had such amazing colors! Boosting said colors beyond the natural is always fun, as well.\r\n<h2>Nature\'s Symmetry</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/natures_symmetry_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Nature&#039;s Symmetry\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-713\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nNature has such a knack for creating beauty everywhere you look.\r\n<h2>Pathways</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/pathways_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Pathways\" width=\"800\" height=\"532\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-714\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2010\r\n\r\nCan you guess what this is? It\'s actually a quilt, transformed into a very three-dimensional looking image.\r\n<h2>Corrugated</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/corrugated_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Corrugated\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-716\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nPart of a Missoula river trail underpass—from an ant\'s perspective, anyway.\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<p>I update this page frequently, so check back often to see my most recent photographs!</p>','Industrial & Abstract Photography','Collection of my photographs featuring industrial or abstract themes.','inherit','open','open','','207-revision-v1','','','2014-07-06 17:10:46','2014-07-06 23:10:46','',207,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2014/07/06/207-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(718,1,'2014-07-06 17:24:52','2014-07-06 23:24:52','<h2 class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Category:</strong> Photography</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"firstH1\">Drip, Drip, Drip</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-202\" alt=\"Drip Drip Drip, photography\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/drip_drip_drip_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo as part of a photography assignment for a university class, in which we had to find or create interesting text and letterforms and photograph them. I created and lit this scene in order to accomplish the look and concept I was after.\r\n<h2>China Shipping</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-200\" alt=\"China Shipping, photography\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/china_shipping_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"574\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nWhile out scouting for interesting typography and text to photograph for a typography class, I suddenly happened upon this fantastic truck parked in a downtown Missoula parking lot. What a great find!\r\n<h2>The Color of Rust</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" alt=\"The Color of Rust\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/the_color_of_rust_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nIt\'s amazing what you can find among a bunch of old rusty mining equipment in the middle of an old field in the industrial sector of a Montana town.\r\n<h2>Million Dollar</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" alt=\"Million Dollar\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/million_dollar_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAs I currently live in Jackson Hole, WY, I figured I might as well take a picture of the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=million+dollar+cowboy+bar&client=firefox-a&hs=eoD&rls=org.mozilla:en-US:official&channel=sb&source=lnms&tbm=isch&sa=X&ei=eZi5U8HTDM-myASIqYCwBg&ved=0CAoQ_AUoAw&biw=1540&bih=758#channel=sb&q=million%20dollar%20cowboy%20bar%20sign&revid=1985559828&rls=org.mozilla%3Aen-US%3Aofficial&tbm=isch&imgdii=_\" target=\"_blank\">famous bar</a> every one of the thousands of tourists take pictures of every day—but in a different way.\r\n<h2>Doble V</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-201\" alt=\"Doble V\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doble_v_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nFinding the right crop is what turning a boring apartment complex sign into something unique is all about.\r\n<h2>Symmetry</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-204\" alt=\"Symmetry\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/symmetry_ali_gray.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"629\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2012\r\n\r\nAnother interesting find for my typography photography assignment. Loved the symmetrical and asymmetrical aspects of the inside of this gazebo roof.\r\n\r\n<h2>225</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/doorway_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Doorway\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-710\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2013\r\n\r\nAmazing door to one of the rooms at the Old Faithful Inn in Yellowstone.\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<p>I update this page frequently, so check back often to see my most recent photographs!</p>','Text Photography','Collection of my photographs featuring text & typography themes.','inherit','open','open','','199-revision-v1','','','2014-07-06 17:24:52','2014-07-06 23:24:52','',199,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2014/07/06/199-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(722,1,'2014-07-06 17:35:27','2014-07-06 23:35:27','<h2 class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Category:</strong> Photography</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"firstH1\">Teeth</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/teeth_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Teeth, photography\" width=\"500\" height=\"750\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-706\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2011\r\n\r\nI took this photo at my parents\' house. There is an awesome vintage saw hanging on the side of the log garage, and I couldn\'t resist photographing its gnarly teeth and their sharp contrast against the circular tree rings.\r\n\r\n<h2>Window to the City</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/window_to_the_city-ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Window to the City\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-720\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2014\r\n\r\nTaken from inside the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=portland+convention+center&espv=2&source=lnms&tbm=isch&sa=X&ei=v9y5U6fxBMjeoATY1YKACQ&sqi=2&ved=0CAcQ_AUoAg&biw=1822&bih=943&dpr=0.9\" target=\"_blank\">Portland Convention Center</a>, looking through to downtown.\r\n\r\n<h2>Oxidized</h2>\r\n<img src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/oxidized_ali_gray.jpg\" alt=\"Oxidized, photography\" width=\"500\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-708\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> 2009\r\n\r\nI took this photo at Flathead Lake in Montana. An old, rusty and weathered boat shack on the shore was absolutely perfect for a photo.\r\n<h2>Wi