ay from the town I felt was home, I landed a job and moved to Jackson, Wyoming right after graduating. There, I became a professional web and graphic designer (but it didn\'t include a season ski pass – I\'m still bitter about that). I worked long hours, sat with big-wig clients, fine-tuned my skillset, and learned a ton.\r\n\r\nAfter feeling young and poor for a year and a half, I decided my personal life needed a boost and so moved to Portland, Oregon in late 2013, which has been my home ever since. In Portland, I\'ve met amazing people, worked at a wonderful job at Portland Community College as the sole web designer, and gotten to explore new places in the outdoors. I\'ve taken up ski mountaineering and climbing to add to my already full quiver of outdoor sports (and fill up my basement with gear). I\'ve met a wonderful partner, and made lasting friends. I\'ve continued to hone my design skills through work and freelance projects. I volunteer as a ski tour leader and publication content editor for our local climbing organization, and take my camera out every weekend. I cuddle with my kitty with a good book when it rains. What more can you ask for?\r\n\r\n[/expand]\r\n<h2 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">I\'ve got the experience</h2>\r\n<div style=\"font-size: 14px;\">[col size=\"one_half\"]<strong>2008 - 2012</strong>\r\nBachelor of Arts in <a href=\"http://www.umt.edu/mediaarts/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Media Arts</a>\r\nThe University of Montana – Missoula, MT\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2013-present</strong>\r\nWeb designer\r\n<a href=\"https://www.pcc.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Portland Community College</a> – Portland, OR\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2011-2013</strong>\r\nWeb and graphic designer\r\n<a href=\"http://www.circ.biz/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Circ Design &amp; Media</a> – Jackson, WY\r\n\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col size=\"one_half_last\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>2011 - 2012</strong>\r\nStudent web designer\r\n<a href=\"https:/