rkling water, and cold craft beer.</li>\r\n 	<li>Spend my free time reading, often biographies of badass outdoor women.</li>\r\n 	<li>Love being outside more than practically everything else.</li>\r\n 	<li>Don’t style my hair. Pretty much ever.</li>\r\n 	<li>Don\'t like celery, potatoes, or mustard – most other foods are game. Bread is my favorite.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/col]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"button\" href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/contact/\">Contact me</a></p>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','20-revision-v1','','','2019-08-17 14:07:20','2019-08-17 21:07:20','',20,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2019/08/17/20-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1254,1,'2019-08-17 14:28:58','2019-08-17 21:28:58','<h2>Portland Alpine Festival</h2>\n<p class=\"fineprint\">Please note: I designed these logos for a design contest, which I did not win. But I think the logos showcase my graphic design style well, so I chose to include them in my portfolio. The designs are in no way tied to the Portland Alpine Festival, the Mazamas, or Grivel.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n[col size=\"one_half\" class=\"text-right portfolio-item-info\"]\n\n<strong>Category:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/portfolio-category/graphic-design/\">Graphic design</a>, <a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/portfolio-category/illustration/\">illustration</a>\n<strong>Client:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.portlandalpinefest.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Portland Alpine Festival</a> (unused design)\n<strong>Year:</strong> 2017\n\n[/col]\n\n[col size=\"one_half_last\"]\n\nThe designs on this page, which I entered into a logo design contest for the 2017 Portland Alpine Festival, show my train of thought for using related imagery in a variety of compositions.\n\n[/col]\n<h3>Climb (and design) on</h3>\nThe Portland Alpine Festival is a yearly event that <em>\"brings the community together for a series of clinics, seminars, and experiences that celebrate our shared interest in enjoying and preserving mountain environments.\"</em> From talks given by famous athletes to clinics introducing climbing or rescue skills, the event is for anyone interested in mountain recreation.\n<h4>To contest or not to contest</h4>\nI\'m apprehensive about entering design contests. They\'ve burned me in the past, and no one likes doing work for free. The whole concept can make it easy for designers to be taken advantage of. So when I saw an announcement about the PAF logo design content, my first instinct was a hard pass.\n\nBut then I thought about it, and figured that designing something that personally interests me seemed worthwhile, even if I was doing the work for free. I could have some fun. I volunteer regularly for the organization who puts on the festival, anyway.\n\nThe contest called for a logo to be used in a wide variety of places. The entered logo should be:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Full color for the PAF website, Mazamas website, and Mazama Bulletin magazine.</li>\n 	<li>Single color for the t-shirt, and for over the top of a photograph online or in print.</li>\n 	<li>Scalable for small and large use.</li>\n</ul>\nThe following concepts are what I came up with. My goal was to design something fun, inspired by vintage clothing tags or patches.\n<h3>Concept 1</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1206\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/paf1.png\" alt=\"PAF logo design 1\" width=\"1495\" height=\"768\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1210\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/paf-t-shirt.png\" alt=\"Concept 1 t-shirt\" width=\"900\" height=\"854\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1211\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/concept-1-magazine.png\" alt=\"Concept 1 magazine\" width=\"1000\" height=\"692\" />\n<h3>Concept 2</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1208\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/paf2.png\" alt=\"PAF logo design 2\" width=\"1495\" height=\"768\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1215\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/paf-t-shirt2.png\" alt=\"Concept 2 t-shirt\" width=\"900\" height=\"854\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1212\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/concept-2-magazine.png\" alt=\"Concept 2 magazine\" width=\"1000\" height=\"692\" />\n<h3>Concept 3</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1209\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/paf3.png\" alt=\"PAF logo design 3\" width=\"1495\" height=\"768\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1214\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/paf-t-shirt3.png\" alt=\"Concept 3 t-shirt\" width=\"900\" height=\"854\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1213\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/concept-3-magazine.png\" alt=\"Concept 3 magazine\" width=\"1000\" height=\"692\" />\n<h3>Concept 4</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1217\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/paf4.png\" alt=\"Other PAF concept\" width=\"1495\" height=\"768\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1256\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/paf-t-shirt4.png\" alt=\"Concept 4 t-shirt\" width=\"900\" height=\"854\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1255\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/concept-4-magazine.png\" alt=\"Concept 4 magazine\" width=\"1000\" height=\"692\" />','Portland Alpine Festival','','inherit','closed','closed','','1096-autosave-v1','','','2019-08-17 14:28:58','2019-08-17 21:28:58','',1096,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2019/08/17/1096-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1255,1,'2019-08-17 14:27:51','2019-08-17 21:27:51','','concept-4-magazine','','inherit','open','closed','','concept-4-magazine','','','2019-08-17 14:28:05','2019-08-17 21:28:05','',1096,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/concept-4-magazine.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1256,1,'2019-08-17 14:27:54','2019-08-17 21:27:54','','paf-t-shirt4','','inherit','open','closed','','paf-t-shirt4','','','2019-08-17 14:28:14','2019-08-17 21:28:14','',1096,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/paf-logo/paf-t-shirt4.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1259,1,'2019-08-17 15:03:34','2019-08-17 22:03:34','','pcc-homepage-desktop','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-homepage-desktop','','','2019-08-17 15:03:34','2019-08-17 22:03:34','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-homepage-desktop.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1258,1,'2019-08-24 15:51:04','2019-08-24 22:51:04','[full_portfolio]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1259\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1416\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1259 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-homepage-desktop.png\" alt=\"Portland Community College homepage - desktop web design\" width=\"1416\" height=\"880\" /> pcc.edu homepage[/caption]\n\n[/full_portfolio]\n\n<h2>PCC website</h2>\n[col size=\"one_half\" class=\"text-right portfolio-item-info\"]\n\n<strong>Category:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/portfolio-category/web-design/\">Web design</a>\n<strong>Client:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.pcc.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Portland Community College</a>\n<strong>Year:</strong> 2013-present\n\n[/col]\n\n[col size=\"one_half_last\"]\n\nWorking as the one-and-only web designer for Portland Community Collage since 2013, I\'ve done a complete overhaul of the pcc.edu website and front-end codebase. I maintain the CSS libraries and content components for our team and a large body of editors.\n\n[/col]\n<h3>Web design for a higher purpose</h3>\nPortland Community College (PCC) is Oregon\'s largest higher education institution, serving approximately 71,000 students. What does that mean from a design perspective? That my team and I have to provide a website that is usable for everyone, everywhere. It needs to be responsive, fully accessible, look good, and be intuitive to use on any semi-modern device. Sound like a tall order? It is.\n\n[full_portfolio]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1262\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"2000\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1262 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-homepage-spread.png\" alt=\"PCC homepage on phone and tablet\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1091\" /> pcc.edu homepage mobile web designs[/caption]\n\n[/full_portfolio]\n\nOur thousands and thousands of pages need to be easy to navigate, and our thousands and thousands of users (current students, prospective students, faculty, staff, parents, partners, and the public) need to be able to find what they need, fast.\n\nOur team of seven, including me, do keep busy.\n\n[full_portfolio]\n\n[col size=\"one_half\"]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1264\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1066\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1264 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-programs.png\" alt=\"PCC programs page - desktop web design\" width=\"1066\" height=\"879\" /> Academic Programs page[/caption]\n\n[/col]\n\n[col size=\"one_half_last\"]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1263\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1066\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1263 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-programs-mobile.png\" alt=\"PCC programs page - mobile\" width=\"1066\" height=\"879\" /> Academic Programs page - mobile web designs[/caption]\n\n[/col]\n\n[/full_portfolio]\n<h3>Usability is at the heart of what we do</h3>\nAlongside my team members (our manager, two developers, one web analyst, and two content specialists), I work every day to make our suite of websites and applications as usable as possible. Ease of navigation, accessibility, a clean design, and student-focused content are some of our largest goals when working on the website ourselves and with staff around the college.\n\n[full_portfolio]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1267\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"2000\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1267 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-content-spread.png\" alt=\"PCC content page examples on mobile\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1091\" /> Get started mega menu, content page, tile layout[/caption]\n\n[/full_portfolio]\n<h3>Organize, organize, organize</h3>\nI\'ve created an assortment of content components to make sure that content is easy to scan and read. The correct use of headings is important, but the ability to break up content with callouts, lists, tabs, expandable accordions, images or icons, calls to action buttons, and more are even better.\n\n[full_portfolio]\n\n[col size=\"one_half\"]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1265\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1066\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1265 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-about.png\" alt=\"PCC about page\" width=\"1066\" height=\"879\" /> Basic content page[/caption]\n\n[/col]\n\n[col size=\"one_half_last\"]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1266\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1066\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1266 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-financial-aid.png\" alt=\"PCC financial aid page web design\" width=\"1066\" height=\"879\" /> Content page with various organizational components[/caption]\n\n[/col]\n\n[col size=\"one_half\"]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1269\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1066\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1269 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-tabs.png\" alt=\"PCC tab interface web design\" width=\"1066\" height=\"879\" /> Tab interface and callout box[/caption]\n\n[/col]\n\n[col size=\"one_half_last\"]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1268\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1066\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1268 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-open-sesame.png\" alt=\"PCC accordion / expandable sections interface\" width=\"1066\" height=\"879\" /> Expandable accordion sections[/caption]\n\n[/col]\n\n[/full_portfolio]\n<h3>Related projects</h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/portfolio/mypcc-portal/\">MyPCC student portal</a></li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/portfolio/pcc-graphics/\">PCC graphic design and illustration</a></li>\n</ul>','PCC website','','inherit','closed','closed','','1220-autosave-v1','','','2019-08-24 15:51:04','2019-08-24 22:51:04','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/2019/08/17/1220-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1260,1,'2019-08-17 15:13:15','2019-08-17 22:13:15','','pcc-homepage-desktop2','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-homepage-desktop2','','','2019-08-17 15:13:15','2019-08-17 22:13:15','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-homepage-desktop2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1261,1,'2019-08-17 15:12:48','2019-08-17 22:12:48','','pcc-homepage-desktop3','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-homepage-desktop3','','','2019-08-17 15:12:48','2019-08-17 22:12:48','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-homepage-desktop3.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1263,1,'2019-08-17 17:39:11','2019-08-18 00:39:11','','pcc-programs-mobile','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-programs-mobile','','','2019-08-17 17:39:57','2019-08-18 00:39:57','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-programs-mobile.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1262,1,'2019-08-17 17:20:48','2019-08-18 00:20:48','','pcc-homepage-spread','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-homepage-spread','','','2019-08-17 17:20:48','2019-08-18 00:20:48','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-homepage-spread.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1264,1,'2019-08-17 17:39:13','2019-08-18 00:39:13','','pcc-programs','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-programs','','','2019-08-17 17:39:26','2019-08-18 00:39:26','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-programs.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1265,1,'2019-08-17 18:52:02','2019-08-18 01:52:02','','pcc-about','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-about','','','2019-08-17 18:52:02','2019-08-18 01:52:02','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-about.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1266,1,'2019-08-17 18:48:17','2019-08-18 01:48:17','','pcc-financial-aid','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-financial-aid','','','2019-08-17 18:48:35','2019-08-18 01:48:35','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-financial-aid.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1267,1,'2019-08-17 18:56:02','2019-08-18 01:56:02','','pcc-content-spread','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-content-spread','','','2019-08-17 18:56:13','2019-08-18 01:56:13','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-content-spread.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1268,1,'2019-08-17 19:27:31','2019-08-18 02:27:31','','pcc-open-sesame','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-open-sesame','','','2019-08-17 19:28:12','2019-08-18 02:28:12','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-open-sesame.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1269,1,'2019-08-18 14:44:50','2019-08-18 21:44:50','','pcc-tabs','','inherit','open','closed','','pcc-tabs','','','2019-08-18 14:44:50','2019-08-18 21:44:50','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/pcc-tabs.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1270,1,'2019-08-17 19:35:46','2019-08-18 02:35:46','','portland-community-college','','inherit','open','closed','','portland-community-college','','','2019-08-17 19:35:56','2019-08-18 02:35:56','',1220,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/pcc-website/portland-community-college.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1271,1,'2019-08-24 14:31:42','2019-08-24 21:31:42','[full_portfolio]\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1277\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/operation-alpine-logo/operation-alpine.png\" alt=\"Operation Alpine logo graphic design\" width=\"1640\" height=\"924\" />\r\n\r\n[/full_portfolio]\r\n<h2>Operation Alpine logo and t-shirt design</h2>\r\n[col size=\"one_half\" class=\"text-right portfolio-item-info\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/portfolio-category/graphic-design/\">Graphic design</a>\r\n<strong>Client:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/OperationAlpine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Operation Alpine</a>\r\n<strong>Year:</strong> 2018\r\n\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col size=\"one_half_last\"]\r\n\r\nPartly to help out a friend, mostly to support a group whose mission I wholeheartedly support – getting LGBTQ individuals and allies out on the ski slopes together, a place where they are historically and drastically underrepresented – I created a logo and t-shirt to show off the group\'s identity.\r\n\r\n[/col]\r\n<h3>Rainbows in the mountains</h3>\r\nWhat do you think of when asked to describe a skier or snowboarder? White? Definitely. Affluent and good-looking? Yep. Brown, heavier-set, or non-binary? Probably not. As a relatively thin and ok-looking white girl, I often struggle with my privilege in the mountains, and seek out chances to help those who don\'t have that inherent privilege to 1) get out there in the first place, and 2) get the support and recognition they deserve while there.\r\n\r\nThis logo and t-shirt design was one opportunity I jumped at (along with hitting the slopes with those it represents whenever I can).\r\n\r\n[full_portfolio]\r\n\r\n[col size=\"one_half\"]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1276\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"900\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1276 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/operation-alpine-logo/operation-alpine-tshirt-white.png\" alt=\"Operation Alpine t-shirt design in white\" width=\"900\" height=\"854\" /> T-shirt featuring a rainbow Mt. Hood – white[/caption]\r\n\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col size=\"one_half_last\"]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1275\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"900\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1275 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/operation-alpine-logo/operation-alpine-tshirt-black.png\" alt=\"Operation Alpine t-shirt design in black\" width=\"900\" height=\"854\" /> T-shirt featuring a rainbow Mt. Hood – black[/caption]\r\n\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1279\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1920\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1279 size-full\" src=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/operation-alpine-logo/operation-alpine-alt-logos.png\" alt=\"Operation Alpine alternate logo design ideas\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1920\" /> Alternate logo ideas[/caption]\r\n\r\n[/full_portfolio]','Operation Alpine','','publish','closed','closed','','operation-alpine-logo-tshirt','','','2019-08-24 15:51:23','2019-08-24 22:51:23','',0,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/?post_type=portfolio&#038;p=1271',0,'portfolio','',0),(1276,1,'2019-08-24 14:32:11','2019-08-24 21:32:11','','operation-alpine-tshirt-white','','inherit','open','closed','','operation-alpine-tshirt-white','','','2019-08-24 14:33:02','2019-08-24 21:33:02','',1271,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/operation-alpine-logo/operation-alpine-tshirt-white.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1277,1,'2019-08-24 14:32:12','2019-08-24 21:32:12','','operation-alpine','','inherit','open','closed','','operation-alpine','','','2019-08-24 14:32:21','2019-08-24 21:32:21','',1271,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/operation-alpine-logo/operation-alpine.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1278,1,'2019-08-24 15:49:15','2019-08-24 22:49: