19-08-25 19:20:20','',0,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/the-natural-world/ali-gray-nature-photography-25.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1350,1,'2022-05-13 11:21:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2022-05-13 11:21:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/?p=1350',0,'post','',0),(1348,1,'2021-08-23 08:57:44','2021-08-23 15:57:44','','choose-your-own-adventure','','inherit','open','closed','','choose-your-own-adventure','','','2021-08-23 08:57:44','2021-08-23 15:57:44','',0,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/choose-your-own-adventure.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1326,1,'2019-09-25 17:00:28','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<h2>Photography</h2>\r\n[col size=\"one_half\" class=\"text-right portfolio-item-info\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Category:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.iamalidesign.com/portfolio-category/graphic-design/\">Photography</a>\r\n<strong>Client:</strong> Personal\r\n<strong>Year:</strong> Various\r\n<strong>Camera:</strong> Sony a6000, iPhone 6\r\n\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col size=\"one_half_last\"]\r\n\r\nSomething about photography in general here.\r\n\r\n[/col]\r\n<h3>The natural world</h3>\r\nThe natural world is where I feel most at home, and nature photography helps me capture some of that feeling. Looking at photos of a breathtaking landscape or other natural feature, especially when I’m stuck in a man-made box looking at a computer screen, can calm me down like almost nothing else (except petting a cat, of course).\r\n<h3>Furry (and feathery) friends</h3>\r\nAnimals make such rewarding, if challenging, subjects. The pets in our homes and the wildlife out in nature are all dear to my heart, and waiting for the right moment for a meaningful capture is a wonderful way to pass the time.\r\n<h3>Up close and into the abstract</h3>\r\nSeeing familiar things from a different perspective gives them a completely new meaning and context in the world. Inspecting various angles, distances, and heights can really change your perception of the recognizable. Capturing an image that partially or completely abstracts the familiar is an even more extreme exploration of the same concept.\r\n<h3>People and urban spaces</h3>\r\nAdmittedly, I\'m intimidated by photographing people, preferring to stand back and hide my actions rather than face the situation head-on. It\'s something I\'m trying to overcome. Instead, I find more solace in trying to capture the human-made – our urban spaces and designs void of individual characters.\r\n\r\n[full_portfolio]\r\n\r\n[instagram-feed showheader=false]\r\n\r\n[/full_portfolio]','Photography','','draft','closed','closed','','photography','','','2019-09-25 17:00:28','2019-09-26 00:00:28','',0,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/?post_type=portfolio&#038;p=1326',0,'portfolio','',0),(1327,1,'2019-08-25 15:09:40','2019-08-25 22:09:40','','Playing with motion and long exposures. I had the nice camera from MAR','Playing with motion and long exposures. I had the nice camera from MAR','inherit','open','closed','','playing-with-motion-and-long-exposures-i-had-the-nice-camera-from-mar','','','2019-08-25 15:09:40','2019-08-25 22:09:40','',1326,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/up-close-personal/ali-gray-macro-photography-01.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1328,1,'2019-08-25 15:09:42','2019-08-25 22:09:42','','Saw and log','Saw and log','inherit','open','closed','','saw-and-log','','','2019-08-25 15:09:42','2019-08-25 22:09:42','',1326,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/up-close-personal/ali-gray-macro-photography-02.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1329,1,'2019-08-25 15:09:43','2019-08-25 22:09:43','','Pretty little creekside flowers','Pretty little creekside flowers','inherit','open','closed','','pretty-little-creekside-flowers','','','2019-08-25 15:09:43','2019-08-25 22:09:43','',1326,'https://www.iamalidesign.com/wp-content/uploads/up-close-personal/ali-gray-macro-photography-03